title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
Mix 2 teaspoons of mix in 1 cup hot water.

title: lemon pineapple fluff
directions: Prepare Jell-O until thickened, but not set.
Add marshmallows, drained pineapple, Cool Whip and instant lemon pudding (dry).
Mix well.

title: quick cobb salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and basil.
In salad bowl, toss greens with dressing.
Top with remaining ingredients, arranging in pie shaped sections.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add buttermilk.
Chill again.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes. Saut bacon until crisp. Remove bacon; drain off except 3 or 4 tablespoons of drippings. Mix together flour, cider vinegar, onion, water, sugar and salt to simmering. Put hot potatoes into vinegar mixture and stir until they appear glazed; they should not be dry. Crumble bacon and stir into salad. Adjust seasonings. Top with sliced eggs. Let stand several hours or overnight to blend. Reheat or serve chilled.

title: country style corn bread dressing
directions: Boil onion and celery in water until tender.
Combine all other ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour onion and celery (undrained) over bread mixture.
Stir well.
If mixture seems too dry, add more chicken broth or 1 cup milk.
Place mixture in buttered baking dish and bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients; chill.
This is so simple, you will love it!

title: escalloped onions
directions: Cook onions in salt water until tender.
Save 1 1/2 cups of the water.
Blend water, flour, cheese and pepper into a sauce. Pour over onions in casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Add more milk if necessary to make mixture soupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold each of the ingredients into the Cool Whip.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add all ingredients and simmer a few minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring, if desired.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm.

title: pocket sandwich filling
directions: Mix loosely.
Spoon into pocket bread.
Serve cold.
Or warm in microwave 30 seconds or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Soften butter; add Ricotta and blend with fork until creamy. Add vanilla and sugar and beat well.
Add egg and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Place 1 teaspoon each on a greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 (or more) minutes.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Saute beef, onions, green peppers and garlic until tender. Add water, tomato paste and salt.
Reserve one cup.
Add beans and mushrooms to remaining mixture.
Simmer and pour into baking dish.

title: chili soup
directions: Chop the onion and garlic and brown in olive oil.
Add hamburger and cook slowly until browned.
Add all remaining ingredients, except the beans, and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add the chili beans and let cook.

title: baked beans
directions: Braise in oil the onion and bell pepper until done.
Mix the first four ingredients well and then crumble bacon into mixture; cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet & sour tuna
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. In sauce, combine 1/3 cup of the pineapple juice, pineapple tidbits, green pepper strips, chicken bouillon cube and water. Heat to boiling and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: turkey-barley soup
directions: In 6 or 8-quart pot, cover beans with 4 cups water.
Cover and bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and let beans stand, covered, 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Drain, rinse and return to pot.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix for 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 large or 4 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May need to tent foil over bread 15 minutes before done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground cranberries, marshmallows and sugar; let set overnight, then add diced apple, seedless grapes, nutmeats and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in lots of water until done.
Scoop chicken out. Boil the spaghetti in chicken broth.
Drain.
Save 2 cups broth. Dice onion and celery and saute with margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cajun-style seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients and use to season pork, fish or other meats.
Makes 1/2 cup.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 14 minutes.

title: super nachos
directions: Fry ground beef and onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Spread refried beans in shallow baking dish.
Top with meat and green chilies.
Sprinkle the chilies over the beans and meat. Cover evenly with cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.

title: pizza bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: florida snowball
directions: Blend well.
Form into ball, wrap tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in 3/4 cup grated coconut.
Serve with crackers.

title: rummer's hip patters
directions: Melt first three ingredients over hot water. Mix the rest of the ingredients together by hand. Press 2/3 of batter into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Pour chocolate mixture over batter mixture and then spoon the rest of the batter over the chocolate mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Clean strawberries; mash lightly and sweeten.
Save a few pretty ones for garnish.
Set oven at 450° to preheat.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into large mixer bowl.
Add shortening.
Put egg into small mixer bowl.
Beat on high speed 1/4 minute.
Add milk.
Remove from mixer.
Blend shortening and flour on low speed until like cornmeal, then add milk mixture. Beat only until blended.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bottom layer:
Cook squash and onion together about 10 minutes; drain.
Put into casserole dish.

title: mom's plum duff
directions: Blend sugar, shortening and prunes into eggs.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend flour, salt and soda; stir into prune mixture.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart steamed pudding mold (available from Williams Sonoma Stores). Secure lid of mold and steam 1 hour.
(Note:
If you don't have a steamer you can use
a Dutch oven filled halfway with water.) Place the mold on a rack in the middle of the pan and cover. Serve hot with Creamy Sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper; dredge beef slices in flour mixture.
Pound with meat mallet to tenderize.
Place one slice of bacon on top of each meat slice; top this with one onion wedge. Roll up beef with bacon and onion inside; secure with toothpicks. Repeat for other meat slices.
Brown bundles in butter or margarine in Dutch oven, using high heat.
After browning, reduce to low temperature, add water to almost cover beef and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until done, turning beef occasionally.
This makes its own gravy.

title: lazy man's dessert
directions: In a large pan (9 x 13-inch), pour in the syrup, then the water.
Do not mix the two together!
Cover the surface with as many marshmallows as needed.
Mix the cake mix according to package directions and pour over marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve while warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Cook onions slowly in butter until soft.
Add crabmeat and soup and cook 15 minutes.
Serve with plenty of Ritz crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Then add all ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Crush crackers and put in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Then put broccoli mixture in pan and sprinkle on some cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli & corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place reserved crackers and cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: mushroom meat puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup.
Brown in hot fat; pour off fat.
Put soup and water over meat balls and simmer 20 minutes. (I use
an iron skillet.)

title: momma's crab dip
directions: Begin with softened cream cheese and start mixing in the additional ingredients one at a time until all mixed well. Serve with your choice of cracker.

title: no-bake cornflake cookies
directions: Cook 1 cup lite Karo syrup with 1 cup sugar.
Boil to candy stage.
(Drop spoonful into cup of cold water to check; if it holds together, it's done.)
Add peanut butter.
Pour entire mixture over cornflakes and mix together.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs (Tupperware cold cut keeper is ideal).

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake, following directions.
Mix together the cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon onto cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add
all ingredients in a 3 quart Visionware pot.
Cook in microwave at 4 minute intervals.
Stir after each 4 minutes until thickens.
It
will
probably
take 20 minutes to cook. You
can also
cook with a double boiler.
Add vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: warm pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except spaghetti.
Keep spaghetti warm; toss and serve warm with meal.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oklahoma millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered wax paper.
Let cool. Melt paraffin with chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip pecan clusters in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients with mixer in medium-size mixing bowl.
Add shrimp.
Make ahead to let it sit a few days for better flavor.
Serve at room temperature.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown beef; drain and add soup mix.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Saute in salad oil, onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef. Cook until meat and other mixture is done.
Add salt, pepper, corn and soup.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: jamaican bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine base ingredients at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumbs.
Press remaining crumbs into prepared pan.

title: bread soup
directions: Put butter in large pot; add onions, carrots and celery.
Stir till hot.
Add bread.
Stir add water or stock. cook for about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Defrost bread dough.
Oil cookie sheet.
Stretch dough to fit cookie sheet.
Spread tomato sauce.
Sprinkle oregano to taste. Add cheese and desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian bread sticks
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt, sugar, shortening and half the flour.
Beat vigorously until smooth.
Mix in rest of flour.
Knead on floured cloth-covered board until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Cover; let rise 1 hour, until double in bulk.
Heat oven to 400°.
Divide in half.
Cut each half into 24 pieces.
Roll each into pencil shapes, 6, 8 or 10 inches (depending on how thick you like the sticks).
Place on greased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Brush with beaten egg (add 1 tablespoon water to 1 egg).
Sprinkle with sesame, celery or poppy seed, corn meal or coarse salt.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 48.

title: chili-chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in hot oil in a Dutch oven until chicken is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, pinto beans, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle stew into individual serving bowls; top each serving with shredded cheese and remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: no peek coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix with pudding mix.
Prepare according to directions on cake mix package.
Bake in two layers.
Cool.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add onions to 1 tablespoon bacon drippings; cook until tender.
Blend in cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.
Blend in sugar and vinegar.
Add beans.
Heat.
Top with bacon and egg.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat skillet with 3 Tbsp oil. Drop mixture by Tablespoonful into skillet on medium high heat. Turn and brown on both sides.
Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: serve yourself tostadas
directions: Brown beef in large saucepan, drain; add Manwich and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Layer chips on a large platter or on individual plates.
Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Top with cheese, onions and lettuce.
Can also top with sour cream, hot sauce, kidney beans, just anything that you desire.

title: gramma's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil whole sweet potatoes.
Let cool.
Peel and cut into quarters.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle on sugar, vanilla and water.
Dot potatoes and sugar with butter. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° to 350° until syrup thickens.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, pudding mix and water.
Beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish, if desired.

title: sausage stars
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Fill wontons. Place in muffin tins and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: beef barbecue(sloppy joe)
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly until thickened.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, sugar, margarine, eggs, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, at least 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and flip dough so the greased side is up.
Cover bowl tightly.
Refrigerate from 8 hours to 5 days.

title: fried cheese balls
directions: Make a thick cream sauce by melting the margarine and adding flour and milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.
(You need 1/2 cup sauce.)

Season to taste with salt and pepper, including cayenne. New York State cheese is best but you can use a milder cheese highly seasoned with Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce, etc. Mix in grated cheese and chill mixture thoroughly.
Then shape into small balls.
Roll in fine cracker crumbs.
Dip into beaten egg, then in the crumbs again.
Fry in hot oil in a deep pan quickly until brown.
(Brown quickly or they will split open.) Keep warm in a 150° oven or until enough are ready to serve.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Take two whole gingersnaps and take a scoop of ice cream and put it in between the gingersnaps.
If you are not going to eat it now, wrap it individually in plastic wrap and place it in the freezer.

title: texas sparkler
directions: When ready to serve, pour the thawed juice into a large pitcher.
Add gradually, stirring constantly until dissolved, confectioners sugar.
Add the chilled ginger ale; mix thoroughly. Put ice cubes into tall glasses.
Fill each with ginger ale mixture.
Serve with snacks such as potato chips or salted nuts. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
Roll dough into small balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes, then dust with confectioners sugar.

title: italian chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour spaghetti sauce over chicken. Continue to bake until chicken is completely done and sauce is heated through.
Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven to melt cheese and brown top.
Serve.

title: caesars salad "delicioso"
directions: In large salad bowl, beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients. Before serving, mix in romaine lettuce.

title: peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat good.
Stir in peanut butter, then other dry ingredients.
Form into balls. Press with back of fork to make a crisscross.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour pie filling in baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: classic burgers to grill
directions: Combine the beef, salt, pepper, cheese, ketchup and onions and shape into 5 patties.
Grill to desired doneness and serve on toasted buns.
May be done in a skillet.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: In a large pot, combine beans, rice, tomatoes and water.
In skillet, fry bacon, onions and garlic until well cooked.
Add with drippings to bean mixture. Add seasonings. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add water, 1/2 cup at a time, as needed during cooking.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Beat together oil, melted butter, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Fold in flour, allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, bananas, cranberry liqueur, cranberry sauce and walnuts or pecans.
Bake in two loaf pans for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well. Combine all dry ingredients and add to cream mixture, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: spinach bread
directions: Cook spinach as directed, then squeeze dry. Cook onion in margarine until tender. Add mushrooms, cheese and Tabasco. Spread on French bread and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix first six ingredients in a bowl. Stir in chips and pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake for 45 minutes.

title: spicy monterey rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, rice and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 3 to 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pistachio and coconut salad
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a
casserole
dish,	mix
the
green beans, mushroom soup, milk, pimento,
salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until
bubbly.
Add
can of dried onion rings to top of casserole.	Place back in oven for 5 minutes.
Also can cook in microwave oven for 10 to 15 minutes on High.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine Russian dressing and apricot preserves.
Over chicken in baking dish, spread 1/3 dressing and preserves mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Every 1/2 hour add 1/3 more mixture until done.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple to boiling point.
Add jello.
Chill until partially set.
Mix with cream cheese.
Fold in beaten whipping cream and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: beefy noodle dinner
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, garlic and parsley in large skillet; cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring frequently.
Drain well.
Stir in tomato paste, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add noodles, cover and cook 20 minutes or until noodles are done, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook oleo, eggs and sugar until almost boiling.
Scorches easily. Pour over wafer crumbs.
Put pecans and bananas over this.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas and sprinkle with 1/2 cup cookie crumbs.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken pieces in mixture of flour and seasonings. Brown chicken in hot oil until golden.
Remove chicken from pan and drain off most of the oil.
Brown onion and garlic slightly in pan.
Drain off all oil.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Mix well the 3 cups nuts with mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet
1-inch apart.
Cook 30 minutes at 250°.
Do not open
oven door
while
cooking!
Turn
off oven and leave 30 minutes.
Pour out
on wax paper and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: grandad's pork chop casserole
directions: Combine salt, thyme and pepper.
Put on chops and brown in shortening.
Sprinkle rice in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add chops, bay leaf and beans.
Pour on undiluted soup and 1 1/2 soup cans of water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350` for 1 1/4 hours.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Put these on the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Boil all in saucepan.
Dip out 1/3 mixture and put in cobbler dish.

title: sweet sour sausage
directions: In pan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cold water and cornstarch.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in paprika. Cook sausages; cut into small pieces.
Add to mixture.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Spoon Russian dressing and apricot preserves over chicken.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over other ingredients.
Use 1/4 cup of water to clean out jars from dressing and preserves; pour over chicken casserole.
Place pineapple on each piece of chicken to garnish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and continue baking for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Let come to a boil for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove and add last 2 ingredients. Pour on top of graham crackers.
Let set overnight or all day in refrigerator.

title: nanny's banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan. Cook until thick and create layer vanilla wafer, bananas and pudding. Top with marshmallow meringue.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients.
Sift next 4 ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into small 1-inch balls, then roll in granulated sugar (red and green sugar for Christmas).
Do not flatten.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes in a 350° or 375° oven.

title: rice with mushrooms and onions
directions: *Scrubbed red-skinned potatoes, sweet potatoes, turnips or carrots and/or peeled rutabagas or sweet parsnips.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle 1/3 of the mixture into the pie shell. Add peaches and sprinkle with the remaining sugar and flour mixture. Pour heavy cream over the top. Move peaches around a bit with a fork so that the cream completely covers the peaches. Bake for 45 minutes. Serve hot or cool on rack. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber slaw
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onions with salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Mix remaining ingredients well.
Squeeze out cucumbers and onions and add to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: black-eyed pea and sausage soup
directions: In a large heavy pot, make a roux of bacon drippings and flour. Add onion and cook until limp (medium heat).
Add green onions and saute about 2 minutes.
Add celery and seasonings; stir, cooking about 1 minute.
Turn heat to low; add peas, broth, water and sausage.
Stir.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours until peas are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Thirty minutes before serving, 1/4 to 1/2 cup sherry can be added if desired.
Serve with a green salad and French bread or cornbread.

title: zucchini cake(bread)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan (makes a loaf).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: south of the border chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Mix soups, milk, onion and chilies.
Into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer one-half of the tortilla strips, chicken, soup mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients in same order.
Allow to stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix together and pour over crackers.
Toss until coated. Store in container in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and spices.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan greased and floured.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turn out on towel and roll up.
Let cool 1 hour.
Beat cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat smooth.
Unroll cake and spread filling on and roll cake back up.
Wrap in foil and chill or freeze.
Cut off ends and eat 'em.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Add milk gradually.
Frosting should be thick, but not so thick it won't go through a bag.
Now you choose your icing color.

title: moon potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/8-inch thick lengthwise.
Place in cold water.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a paper bag, shake flour and Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Shake 1/2 of potatoes at a time until well coated.
Lay in pan with butter in a single layer.
Bake all at 350° for up to an hour; turn after 1/2 hour.
Crispy and good!

title: cheese cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine cream cheese and milk.
Blend well, then add lemon mix.
It will become thick. Pour into cooled crust and refrigerate.

title: chocaroon pie
directions: *Make 2 pies to use up can.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese in a large bowl until well blended.
Then add jello.
Then add fruit.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix and shake well.
Store unused dressing in refrigerator for future use.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine the next 6 ingredients in a large plastic bag.
Set aside.
Rinse potatoes under cold water, drain well.
Place half of the potatoes in the bag.
Shake well to coat.
Place in a single layer in baking pan. Repeat with remaining potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until tender.
Turn once after 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Roll out on well floured surface.
Sprinkle a little bit of flour on top (don't work into dough).
Roll dough to a thickness of about 1/4 inch.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place cookies on a cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and green onions.
Cook over moderate heat until hot.
Dip tortillas in sauce and then fill with chicken, refried beans, salsa, green chilies, diced olives and a little cheese.
Roll.
Spoon sauce on top of each enchilada and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chili
directions: Chop a big onion and clove of garlic and fry them in a deep pan in a tablespoon of salad oil.
Add a pound of ground beef and cook it slowly until brown.

title: ricky's hamburger special
directions: Make
four beef patties.
Place on individual pieces of aluminum
foil.
On
top of meat, place slices of potatoes and onions.
Wrap each patty securely and bake 25 minutes or until done at 300°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish, mixing well.
Place in oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press graham crackers and 1 stick melted margarine in bottom of pan.
Beat next 4 ingredients for 15 minutes and spread on top of graham crackers.
Slice bananas on top of this.
Place pineapple on top of bananas and spread large container of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with pecans and cherries or fresh strawberries.

title: pea casserole
directions: Cook the peas and saut onion, green pepper and celery in the butter. Add the others and pour into a
1 1/2-quart casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Just before baking, top with crushed cheese crackers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy italian pasta salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Blend the ingredients together in the order they are listed. Put in an ungreased jello roll pan and spread around evenly with your hands.
Break up egg white with a fork and spread over the dough with your hands.
Sprinkle more chopped nuts over the top. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze in quart milk cartons.
Let thaw approximately 4 hours prior to serving.
Place thawed mixture in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Serves approximately 50.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage, onion and pepper together until done.
Add frozen hash browns and cook mixture until hash browns are tender.
Add beaten eggs over this.
Cook until eggs are done, stirring often. Serve on flour tortillas with grated cheese.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion; add 1 pound ground beef.
Brown.
Add mushroom soup.
Season well with garlic, salt, pepper and plenty of Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve on rice or noodles.
Serves about 4.

title: beet jam
directions: Put the beets into a large stainless steel pan and barely cover with water.
Bring to boil over high
heat.
Lower heat and add sugar, lemon juice, grated rind and minced ginger root.
When beets are tender, cook over low heat, stirring frequently until mixture is thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
(I've kept it up to 4 years since a little goes a long way.)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake; use pineapple juice.
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk. Add crushed pineapple.
Spread this topping over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Very fast, yet seems like you fussed.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 tablespoon of the sugar added.
Let set 5 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Add enough plain flour to make a thin dough or batter.
Place in refrigerator overnight or for a few hours before making into rolls.
Then make into rolls, dip in oil or melted butter.
Let rise 1 or 2 hours.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
tags: White Lily baking powder biscuit mix

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon Hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cool.
Top with Dream Whip or other whipped topping, if desired.

title: veggie soup with meat
directions: Cook meat with onion.
Drain fat.
Add to broth.
Drain Veg-All and add to meat and broth.
Add spices and simmer for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in water before cooking.
Then cook 2 to 3 minutes in 1 1/2 cups water.
Drain.
Mix the 2 cans of soup and onion together, then add to the broccoli and mix gently.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and stir in stuffing crumbs. Sprinkle on top of broccoli mixture to cover.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hours.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: chewy cocoa brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cook cake according to box instructions. When it is done poke holes in the cake. Pour eagle brand milk and then caramel over cake and let it seep in. Add Heath brickle. When cake is cool top with cool whip.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in Bake 'N Serve dish 30 minutes.
Serve warm with Triscuits or Trumpets.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce and 1 cup boiling water in blender. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add cranberry mixture and pecans to Jell-O. Divide in half.
Put half of the mixture in an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm in freezer (25 to 30 minutes). Spread sour cream over part that
is set.
Add second half of Jell-O mixture over the sour cream.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: hush puppies(stagecoach inn recipe)
directions: Combine meal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add slowly to 2 1/2 cups boiling water, stirring briskly on low heat until stiff, about 5 minutes.
As soon as mixture is smooth, remove from heat. Stir in butter; cool.
Form into finger shaped rolls.
Fry in 2-inches hot fat at 375° until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Yield:
About 3 dozen hush puppies.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then for 1/2 hour at 350°, or until mixture is set.
Pour on meringue; bake again.

title: quickie salad
directions: Place the cottage cheese in a large bowl.
Add drained, crushed pineapple; mix well.
Add Jell-O; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
May be eaten at once or refrigerated.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese with rest of ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Great with vegetables, chips and snack crackers.

title: pizza burger
directions: Combine meat into 8 to 10 patties, and cook 4 to 5 minutes. Put the hamburger patties in skillet; add sauce and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover and simmer and top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: nana cooper's rolls
directions: Mix together.
Pat down to 1/4-inch and cut with a small cutter.
Brush with butter and fold in half.
Brush again with butter.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, oil, flour and salt and pour over filling. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, with hands.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add yeast to water mixture; let set 5 minutes.
Then add to flour, soda, oil and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon until well combined.
Roll out and cut biscuits and put into baking sheet; let rise about an hour.
Then bake until golden brown.

title: whipped cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth.
Drop dough by about 1/4 cupfuls, 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Whip cream, cut off tops, fill with cream, replace tops, dust with powdered sugar.
Yields 6.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Place apples, sliced, in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle over apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, sugar and butter together and crumble on top of apples.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 400°.
Top will be golden brown when done.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms and water for 20 minutes.
Add wine, base, scallions and thyme.
Melt butter; add flour.
Cook for 5 minutes. Whip flour and butter into mushroom broth until thickens.
Turn off heat; whip in sour cream.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine above and make into 1-inch balls.
Dissolve 2 bouillon cubes in 2 cups water.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to make sauce. Dip meatball in bouillon cube mixture, then fry.

title: cream of chicken soup
directions: Blend margarine and flour in large saucepan.
Stir in milk, cream and broth gradually.
Cook until thickened and bubbly. Stirring constantly, add chicken and seasonings.
Heat to serving temperature.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Garnish with minced chives or parsley.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: gram's spanish rice
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together for 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Makes 3 gallons.
Serves 100 (4-ounce) glasses or 12 quarts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix onion, cheese, garlic, chili powder, soups and tomatoes.
Soften tortillas in chicken broth and line the bottom of the dish. Cover with chicken mixture.
Put into dish in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: herb rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Measure sugar, salt, sage, caraway seed, nutmeg and milk into bowl.
Blend, then add yeast mixture. Pour in about 1/2 of flour and beat until smooth.
Add the egg, shortening and remaining flour and beat again.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Grease 12 large muffin tins, filling half full. Let rise until batter reaches tops of muffin tins.
Bake rolls 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cook apples in microwave until tender and done, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients together and sprinkle over top of apples.
Return to microwave and cook 2 to 3 minutes more or until crust is brown and bubbly.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Crumble first 3 ingredients; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat together pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Yum! Yum!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Precook the chicken by baking or boiling.
Cut up into bite size pieces when cool.
Put this in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Mix soup, water and sour cream and pour over the chicken. Crush the crackers and add the poppy seed and cover the soup mixture.
Melt a stick of butter and pour over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts into mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix and put all ingredients in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Or microwave about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in this order:
bean dip, guacamole dip, taco mixture (mix together sour cream and taco seasoning), chopped green onion, olives, tomatoes, cheese.

title: carob cream dessert
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender.
Add dates.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Cool. Pour into nut granola base and cool in fridge.

title: earl and elizabeth cox's salmon croquettes
directions: Fold chicken soup into salmon and add lemon juice, onions, pepper and coarse cracker crumbs.
Shape into croquettes or patties.
Add milk to the beaten egg.
Roll each croquette in fine cracker crumbs, then in egg mixture and again in the cracker crumbs.

title: italian beef
directions: Place all ingredients into crock-pot and cook on high 6 to 8 hours. When tender enough to pull apart, serve on regular or long hoagie buns.

title: no fat potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes real thin.
Salt and pepper.
Spray iron skillet with cooking spray.
Add potatoes.
Cook in a 450° oven.
Stir about every 10 minutes until desired brownness is reached.

title: doc's smoked fish
directions: Make brine, mixing water and pickling salt until an egg floats.
Place fish in pan so liquid covers fish.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove fish from brine and dry.
Broil in oven a scant 10 minutes per inch (until just about ready to eat). Place on aluminum foil on outdoor grill (use apple wood if possible to create smoke.)
Do not have too hot a fire.
Put grill cover down.
When one side is brown, turn.
When the other side is brown, remove.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: steak in skillet
directions: Coat beef steak pieces with flour; pound into beef.
Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet; push beef to side.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender; drain.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar.
Add cocoa.
Add eggs all at one time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: zesty italian supper
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms and oregano.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in process cheese spread; heat.
Serve over mostaccioli.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil sweet potatoes, chill and mash.
Add sugar, cinnamon, pecans and melted butter.
Form into balls around marshmallows, roll in coconut.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans, wax beans and green beans.
Mix the three kinds of beans.
Dice the onion and add to beans. Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Pour over bean mixture and toss.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: single crust plain pastry
directions: Also makes 4 to 6 tart shells.

title: veal cutlet
directions: Cut veal steak into 6 pieces.
Pound to make thinner.
Dip veal into mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Dip each piece in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Melt half of butter in large frying pan.
Add veal.
Cook over low heat until brown (about 15 minutes).
Remove veal from heat.
Brown the rest of the butter in the frying pan.
Add lemon juice and parsley and stir well.
Pour over veal and serve.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine the potatoes with enough water to cover.
Cook over medium high heat until fork tender.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Beat with an electric mixer until creamy. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix well and add rest of ingredients. Mix until smooth.
Spray baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve. Serve with chips.

title: burritos
directions: Fry hamburger with onion.
When done, place aside on paper towel to drain. Salt. Place refried beans in glass bowl and microwave for approximately 6 minutes (3 minutes, then stir).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a roux by mixing the flour in with the hot oil in a frying pan until browned. Add onion, chopped and garlic.
Stir until soft. Add water and simmer until thick (like gravy).
Add tomato sauce and spices with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in shrimp and heat thoroughly.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 4.

title: forgotten chicken(easy)
directions: Mix celery soup with rice and milk and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lightly salt and pepper chicken
and place on rice mixture.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over all.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until chicken and rice are thoroughly done.

title: low cal - roasted vegetables(low calorie)
directions: In mixing bowl combine potatoes, carrots, peppers and zucchini. Combine the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Drizzle over vegetables.
Stir to coat.
Transfer to greased 13x9x2 baking dish. Bake uncovered at 375 for 30-35 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6 - 3/4 Cup Each; 2 Points.

title: german chocolate cake(the easy way)
directions: Mix all together, beating well.
Grease 2 large layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken. Arrange in shallow baking pan, skin side up. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°, basting every 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: gushy slushy
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 30 seconds or until smooth.
I hope you like it as much as I do. Yields 4 (8 oz.) servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients together in saucepan until the sugar melts and it comes to a boil.
Pour over the meat and steam over low heat until meat is done.
It is best when you brown meat first and pour off grease.
It is good with Spam.

title: vanilla texas sheet cake
directions: In large
saucepan
quart) bring to a boil the margarine and
water.
Remove
from heat; add sugar, flour and salt.
In
small
bowl beat eggs, milk, soda and vanilla.
Add all this
to the mixture in saucepan and beat well.
Pour into pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Chop onions and pepper.
Slice squash (1/4-inch slices). Saute onions in butter until golden brown; add pepper and garlic and cook about 5 minutes.
Layer veggies in a greased 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients except dressing and melted butter. Grease 9
x
x 2 1/2-inch deep dish and put in potato mixture.
Mix dressing and 1/2 cup melted butter and spread over potato mixture.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Break up beef well and mix with other ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes if at room temperature; 45 minutes if cold from refrigerator.

title: hamburger chowder
directions: Brown ground
beef in oil in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients; bring	to boil.
Lower heat and cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until done.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir up.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: christmas rice
directions: Stir all ingredients together into 2-quart casserole; cover. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir several times while cooking. Serves 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Add sauteed mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: chili-phili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread chili over cream cheese.
Spread green chilies over chili. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with favorite garnish:
sliced olives, onions, salsa, etc.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips for dipping.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Combine ingredients until smooth.
To put in bowl, layer ingredients (cookies and mixture), ending with cookies on top.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine beaten egg, sugar, milk and melted shortening.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to bowl containing egg, sugar, milk and shortening.
Mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in pot on stove top until blended.
Great on chicken!

title: "pain au saumon" - salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon. Add 2 cups bread crumbs, eggs, milk, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Delicious when served with a fresh cucumber salad.

title: sorbetto di limone(italian lemonade)
directions: Wash and dry lemons and grate zest from them.
Set zest aside. Squeeze juice and save.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 quart. Add sugar and zest; mix and let rest for 30 minutes.
Strain all and place into ice cream maker and allow to "freeze".
Enjoy!

title: breaded pork chops(cooking for two)
directions: In a bowl, combine egg and barbecue sauce; mix well.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, lemon-pepper and salt.
Dip chops in egg mixture, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place in a greased 8 inch square baking dish. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until juices run clear.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
together and marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp with fork.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: autumn leaf punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Flavor is improved if mixture stands for a day or two.
Reheat to serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shortnin bread(cookies)
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
With a fork, mix in soft butter and work into a smooth dough.
Turn onto a floured table and pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
(If necessary, chill dough for easier handling.)
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° for about 25 minutes until very lightly brown.

title: seasoned fish fillets
directions: Mix mayonnaise and seasonings.
Place fish on greased grill over medium coals or rack of broiler pan, 2 to 4 inches from heat. Brush with 1/2 of the mayo mixture.
Grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining mixture.
Continue grilling (broiling) 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seasoned fish
directions: Bring water to boil.
Mix vinegar, salt and seafood seasoning. Add to boiling water.
Add fish; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: easy pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients with mayonnaise.
Add pepper to taste. Chill.
Best served cold.
Serves 4.

title: long keeping slaw
directions: Combine ingredients and cook for a few minutes and cool.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Melt butter and cool slightly.
Add milk, coconut, nuts and sugar and mix well. Roll into balls.
Melt the chocolate chips with the paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip formed balls of candy. Lift out one at a time.

title: pump-can bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and spices.
Mix pecans. Blend eggs, milk, pumpkin, brown sugar, oil and soda.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Pour into 2 greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Cool 15 minutes before removing from cans.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: blue ribbon overnight rolls
directions: In large bowl mix together yeast, milk and sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix eggs, butter or margarine and salt into yeast mixture.
Mix in flour, 2 cups at a time.
Cover with wax paper. Let dough stand at room temperature overnight.
Next morning, divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a 9 inch round circle. Cut each round into 12 pie-shaped wedges.
Roll up each wedge, starting from wide end to the tip.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Let stand until ready to bake, up to 12 hours.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wild rice and artichoke hearts
directions: Wash and drain wild rice.
Place rice, consomme, water and salt in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Beat 2 eggs slightly and add 1/2 cup milk to each cup of flour.
Add 1/4 cup yellow corn meal, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dip chicken into egg and milk mixture.
Put chicken into bag of flour mixture. Place into deep hot fat.
Fry until chicken is golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix gently to prevent damaging beans.
Cook in covered pot for 1 hour in a 350° oven. Serve to a large group or place in small earthenware pots to reheat in oven later. Freeze to store.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour in 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: pampusky(slovak donuts)
directions: Take egg yolks, melted butter, icing sugar and rum and stir the mixture until you create a foam; add milk, yeast, salt and enough flour so the dough is not too soft or hard.
After the dough rises, you roll it and cut it to different shapes (most often round) and then deep fry in Puritan oil.
When fried crispy, dry on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir remaining ingredients except cinnamon-sugar mixture together.
Add to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place
2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Arrange ingredients in layers in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Serve with corn chips.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour and Parmesan cheese in a plastic bag.
Shake a few potatoes in the bag at a time.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes with a spatula and bake another 30 minutes.

title: lemon vinaigrette
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container.
Serve with a Cobb Salad.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add all dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Start in cold oven.)
Cover with a plate after taking out of oven for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: methodist chicken
directions: Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay pieces of fryer on top of rice; mix all other ingredients together and spoon over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover and continue baking another 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions and peppers in blender. Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices. Bring to a boil. Add pears, onions and peppers. Bring to a boil and cook at reduced heat for 20 minutes. Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: snow white frosting
directions: Microwave on Roast the sugar, water and the Karo or cream of tartar until boiling.
Beat the egg whites to soft peaks.
Add syrup slowly while still beating.
Beat until thick and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Spread on your favorite cake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese together with seasoning.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Knead dough.
Roll out and cut or use a cookie press.
Add 1 tablespoon of water if dough is too stiff. Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: egg nog dessert
directions: Mix gelatin with cold water and dissolve over heat.
Mix with egg nog.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in diced maraschino cherries and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Let set several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Serve.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in square pan.
Top with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: honey-lime dressing
directions: Combine ingredients, whip and chill.
Use over salad greens or broiled fish.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and onions in a skillet.
Put this mixture in a food processor and chop it.
Put in a pan.
Put the kidney beans in the food processor and chop them.
Add them to the pan with the tomato soup and the tomatoes; cook all together.

title: mom's eat your veggies minestrone soup
directions: Cook ground beef; add onion and cook for approximately 3 minutes, stirring.
Add water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and lima beans.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour (until lima beans are tender).
Then add carrots, turnips, celery, tomatoes, bay leaf and basil.
Simmer until veggies are tender (about 30 minutes).
Add cabbage and cook 5 minutes.
Add spinach and cook 5 more minutes.
Taste; season to taste, if needed. Serve hot.
Great anytime!!

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to pkg. directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork and pour Kahula over brownies; set aside.
Whip Jello Mousse according to pkg. directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in food processor or by tapping them with a hammer (in the wrapper).
Break up half the brownies and place in bottom of a glass trifle dish.
Cover with half of mousse, layer with half of candy, then half of whipped topping. Repeat layers.
Enjoy!
It's so good!!
*Note - Instead of the alcohol, you may substitute a mixture of 1 tsp. sugar and 4 Tbsp. left-over black coffee.

title: pecan pie
directions: Allow butter to stand in medium mixing bowl at room temperature until soft.
Add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add eggs and beat gently until blended. Fold in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake in 375° oven on the rack directly below center rack until top is toasted brown and filling is set in center when pie is gently shaken (40 to 50 minutes).

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into two well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.

title: snack mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Serve as a finger snack.

title: lime pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill for 1 hour; top with Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with chocolate sprinkles.
Serves approximately 6.

title: zucchini magnifico
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat pies
directions: Mix well ground beef, pork sausage, red pepper, salt and paprika.
Then add green onions and blades, onions, bell pepper and flour.
Cook slowly.
When almost done, add parsley flakes. Cook a little longer and stir.
Cool and drain while preparing dough.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine flour, milk and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 14 minutes. Yields 1/2 dozen.

title: cajun turkey burgers
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Shape mixture into six 3/4-inch thick patties.
Wrap a strip of bacon around outside of each patty.
Fasten with toothpick.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 15 to 18 minutes or until no pink remains and bacon is done, turning once.
Remove toothpicks before serving.
Serve on wheat buns and top with tomato slices and chili peppers.

title: golden toad
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Serve with peach slice and green cherry garnish.

title: country custard pie
directions: Line the pastry in the pie pan with aluminum foil and weight it down with uncooked beans, rice or with pie weights.
Bake 15 minutes in a 450° oven you've preheated.
Remove the weights and foil and cool.

title: devil's food cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Combine the next 4 ingredients; mix well. Add to the creamed mixture; beat well.
Add flavor; mix well. (The dough will be stiff.)
Chill dough for 30 minutes; shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on oiled cookie sheet and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place 1/2 marshmallow on top of cookies; return to oven for 3 minutes.
Cool on wire rack; frost with Chocolate Icing.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut cake
directions: Stir sour cream, coconut and sugar in large container; let refrigerate overnight.
On the second day, bake cake mix as directed.
Let cool thoroughly.
Split cake into 4 layers.
Put coconut mixture between layers, then add a small container of Cool Whip to the other half of the mixture.
Ice the top and sides with this mixture.
Refrigerate overnight; cut the third day.

title: tomato broth(low calorie)
directions: Combine beef broth, tomato juice and water.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add parsley.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Equals 14 calories or free exchange.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and spices together; add nuts and raisins.
In separate bowl mix sugar, butter, oil and eggs.
Mix all ingredients together and add bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season fryer, cover with water and let cook on low heat about 3 to 4 hours.
Let stand in broth until cool.
Remove chicken from broth and bone.
Saute in skillet 2 sticks of margarine with bell peppers and onions.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; add water if needed.
Do not drain spaghetti.
Add pimento, Velveeta cheese and tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly and cover.
Let stand on warm burner for 30 minutes.
If you desire it to be hotter in taste, add another can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Serves 8 people (or can be frozen for one of those nights I don't want to cook).

title: overnight salad
directions: Using large plastic bowl with a tight cover, put in ingredients in layers as they are listed.
Seal tight.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Toss just before serving.
If you want to use part of this salad, dip straight down and put in another bowl to mix.
Serves quite a group and is great for family night suppers or buffets.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to tenderize. Dip into egg and then into bread crumbs.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese on each cutlet.
Fold in half and brown on all sides until medium brown.
Place in baking dish and add mushroom soup and milk to skillet.
Stir and pour over chicken cutlets. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with noodles.

title: liz's coffee cake(terrific!  the sour cream makes the difference.)
directions: Cream together margarine/butter and sugar.
Fold in sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt. Spoon 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 the topping (listed); add remaining batter and topping as in 1st layer.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Can store in refrigerator wrapped in foil.

title: twin applesauce loaves
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt, cocoa, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and allspice into mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and applesauce.
Beat 200 strokes by hand or with mixer on low.
Add eggs; beat 200 strokes.
Stir in dates, raisins, citron and nuts.
Pour into 2 small loaf cake pans, greased, or 1 large tube cake pan.
Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons of chopped nuts and 1 tablespoon of brown sugar.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cool; remove from pans.

title: hobo dinners
directions: On four 18-inch squares of aluminum foil, divide and place beef in center in patty.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions on top of beef patty.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fold and seal foil. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good on grill; great for camping.

title: holiday sweetbread
directions: Beat yolks and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix yeast and water.
Let set 5 minutes.
Heat milk and butter; cool until lukewarm.
Add milk mixture to egg mixture, yeast and vanilla. Mix in flour; knead 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; punch down. Raise again; punch down.
Shape in regular loaves or braided loaves.
Brush gently with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, dice and measure eggplant.
Cook until tender in small amount of water and salt.
Saute celery and onion until tender. Drain eggplant; add to celery and onion.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg and milk or cream.
Pour in a 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger vegetable medley
directions: Cut potatoes into stew-sized chunks and boil until firmly cooked.
Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet; drain.
Add sauce, green beans and potatoes into skillet.
Cook on low heat approximately 15 minutes.
Top with grated cheese, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops and set aside.
Into a paper bag, put flour, salt, pepper and chops.
Shake bag firmly to coat chops.
Place trimmed fat in frying pan and saute briefly. Remove.
Brown chops in fat remaining in pan, then add apricots, onions and soy sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Uncover. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Simmer 15 more minutes.

title: john ben getty
directions: Brown meat and onions until done.
Add soups and corn; mix well.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and blanch, add to meat mixture.
Grease large baking dish (12 x 18-inch).
Pour in mixture.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Store in cool, dry place up to 6 months.
Dry mix makes about 17 cups.

title: lo-cal cheesaroni beef casserole
directions: Season ground round with garlic salt.
Spread in a shallow layer in a nonstick baking pan.
Broil meat about 2 inches from heat just until surface is brown.
Drain off fat.
Combine browned meat, onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil and chili powder in a large saucepan or kettle.
Bring to boiling; cover. Lower heat; simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently, until sauce is thick.
Cook macaroni 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Toss with cottage cheese.
Spread cottage cheese macaroni mix in bottom of shallow 12 cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon over sauce.
Top with Romano.
Freeze for future use or bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix hamburger with wild rice and seasoning.
Make into small balls.
Mix together mushrooms and tomato soup, undiluted.
Place in glass baking dish.
Pour mushrooms over meat and sauce on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Sift baking powder and sugar, then beat sugar, eggs and butter together.
Add crackers and remaining ingredients.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans and cook at 350° for 30 minutes in preheated oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain the pineapple chunks, then mix all the ingredients together.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: chocolate mint meltaways
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar, add egg and vanilla, blending well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk; blend well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.
Mold dough over patties and cover completely.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute on cookie tray, then remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and Cool Whip until light.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat 5 minutes.

title: dutch pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour with baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Frost cooled cake or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Also delicious just plain.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Beat eggs and milk and add to hot mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl, then serve with the tortilla chips to dip.
Also delicious over garden salad.

title: tortilla beef bake
directions: Cook meat and drain. Add onion and bell pepper. Cook for five minutes; add soup, salsa (or Rotel tomatoes), and corn. In a 2 qt. oiled baking dish, layer meat mixture, cheese, and chips until all is used. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. If desired, you may top with cheese or chips and bake for a few minutes longer.

title: upside-down sticky chocolate cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions on package.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, mix together the brown sugar, cocoa, water and marshmallows.
Pour cake mix mixture over top in pan.
Bake at 350° until the cake is done.
Cut in squares for serving and turn upside down.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until light.
Add flour slowly.
Add vanilla. Scrape sides of bowl and beat for two minutes on medium speed. Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 65 minutes.

title: priscilla's buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
In a large bowl, mix 2 cups warm water, sugar, shortening and salt.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat, then add egg and yeast.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour.
Mix with spoon, about 60 strokes.
Dough will be soft.
Let rise in greased bowl.
Grease top of dough.
Punch down; let rise again.
Form into desired shapes.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° until medium brown, 15 minutes.

title: melon cooler salad
directions: Place cheese and concentrate in blender until well blended. Put melon balls in bowls or glasses and top with mixture.

title: broccoli casserole #3
directions: Cook broccoli as per directions.
Drain and cool completely. Melt 1 stick of butter with cheese.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter in skillet on medium heat.
Add cracker crumbs and brown.

title: cocktail bits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into tiny balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Place meat balls in a chafing dish and cover with barbecue sauce.

title: dieter's special
directions: Place in baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave 8 minutes. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Toss.
Ready to serve.

title: 4-h banana bread(state fair winners book)
directions: Cream butter until soft; gradually add sugar and mix well. Blend in eggs, then bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Bake in 10 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Top with split slightly.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out pizza dough in an oblong shape and sprinkle with Parmesan. Fry pepperoni in frying pan or microwave to remove fat. Lay pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese over entire dough. Roll up dough and fold over ends. Pierce dough with sharp knife every 2-inches across the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken pieces in nonmetal dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
In a saucepan melt butter over low heat.
Add flour and salt.
Add milk and cook slowly.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Add half grated cheese to sauce and stir until melted.
Add macaroni and mix thoroughly. Pour into casserole.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: new bread
directions: Mix and pour in muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese biscuits
directions: Mix margarine and corn oil.
Quarter biscuits and roll in margarine mixture until well coated.
Mix the Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Roll butter coated biscuits in Parmesan mixture.
Place biscuits close together on cookie sheet; bake until barely done, according to directions on can.
(You can put these in a crock-pot on low to keep them warm.)

title: four star microwave chicken divan
directions: Pierce packages of broccoli and partially thaw in package on High 4 1/2 minutes.
Place chicken in 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 7 minutes on High.
Remove chicken and slice in pieces.
Arrange broccoli on bottom of baking dish.
Place slices of chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Remove plastic and sprinkle cheese on top.
Measure bread crumbs.
Add butter.
Heat 1 minute on High; mix well.
Brown under broiler.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix, adding sherbet by spoonfuls last.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until browned; drain fat.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new haven cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; set aside to cool.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour and cocoa, sifted together, alternately with date mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 12 or more.

title: cheese and beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Prepare Velveeta dinner as directed and add tomatoes. Place Velveeta mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Whip first 4 ingredients.
Add beef.
Shape into a ball, then roll into the nuts.
Refrigerate.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: picante sauce
directions: Boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Put dried bread cubes in deep casserole.
Pour melted butter over them.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, tomato puree and water.
Bring to a boil, simmer for 5 minutes and pour the mixture over the bread cubes.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven until the top puffs and browns.
Serve immediately!

title: cucumber sauce or dressing
directions: Peel cucumbers and dice.
Drain moisture from cucumbers.
Mix all ingredients with cucumbers.
Chill and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Spread rolls in a 12-inch ungreased pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch baking pan and seal.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey salad sandwich filling
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and mix well.
Spread between pieces of bread to make sandwiches.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet; fry chicken until browned.
Drain and place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan, saute onion in butter or oleo until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chicken is done, basting occasionally.
Will feed 5 to 7 people.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Soak orange roughy in milk 15 minutes or longer.
Beat 1 egg. Dip fish in egg, then in Italian bread crumbs.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.
Do not turn.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; stir in cranberry sauce, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a 13 x 9-inch container; freeze.
Can be made several days in advance.
(Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.)

title: apricots-stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine apricots, water and sugar.
Set aside. Trim chops and coat with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat the shortening in a skillet and brown the chops on both sides.
Combine apricot mixture, bread cubes, apples, celery, thyme and marjoram.
Mix lightly and season with salt and pepper.
Place fruit stuffing in bottom of casserole and arrange the browned pork chops on top. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours or until chops are well done. Yields 4 servings.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Put rice in a baking dish and add beef consomme.
Add onion.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 45 minutes or until brown and done.
Cook in a tightly covered baking dish.

title: banana-nut raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter/margarine and mix with brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and let stand for 20 minutes at room temperature.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or when top is brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix well and spread in a large cookie sheet.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Blend together and heat in pan.
If too thin, thicken with cornstarch and water.
This may be frozen and reheated.
Serve in chafing dish with chips or crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar, then beat in eggs. Add milk, salt and corn last.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until pudding
is
firm.
If
canned corn is used, add 2 teaspoons flour
for
each
cups
corn and cream it well with butter or margarine and sugar.
Serves 6.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan, cracker crumbs and butter.
Cream until fluffy, powdered sugar, eggs and butter.
Put on top of graham cracker mixture.
Spread over top the pineapple. Slice bananas lengthwise in fourths.
(Strawberries may be used.) Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with walnuts or maraschino cherries, if desired.
Make the day before you wish to serve.

title: popular green bean casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, break up ground beef in very small chunks.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cover.
