Microwave at High (10) for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Drain well. Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, chili powder and salt.
Microwave at High (10) for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Use meat to fill prebaked packaged taco shells, filling about half full.
Finish tacos by topping with 2 or more or the following: shredded lettuce, shredded cheese, chopped tomatoes and chopped onions.
Add hot sauce, if desired.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream white sugar, butter and shortening.
Add vanilla, soda and salt and mix.
Add egg and beat well.
Add milk, flour and rhubarb; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: new soft cookie
directions: Mix oil, sugar, molasses and egg together.
Add flour, soda, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Roll spoonfuls into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, 8 to 10 minutes, in 350° oven.
Cool on rack.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat egg and stir in sugar, oil and orange juice.
Sift in flour, baking powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in nuts and blueberries.

title: diabetic dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Layer a small baking pan with graham crackers.
Spread prepared pudding on top of graham crackers.
Next spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Continue in layers until pudding is used up, ending with Cool Whip on top. Crumble a few graham crackers and sprinkle on top.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Stir in scallions, pepper and tomatoes.
Add Salad Supreme and salad dressing; stir.
Refrigerate for at least several hours, preferably overnight.
The amounts indicated can be increased according to taste.
Optional additions include broccoli flowerets, black olives and vegetables of your choice.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Fresh broccoli should be washed, trimmed and broken into small pieces.
Place broccoli in medium saucepan and add next 6 ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove some florets and set aside for garnish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat until well mixed the sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 325° for one hour.
Makes two regular loaves.

title: microwave sweet pickles
directions: You can use 1/4 teaspoon pickling spice too.

title: turnips
directions: Let meat boil until tender.
Add turnips to this meat and broth.
After turnips have boiled and gone down, put lard and remaining seasonings in.
If needed, may add bacon grease to taste.

title: angel food candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat to 300°. Stir all the time so it will not burn.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Stir well and pour into a well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, break into chunks and dip in melted chocolate.

title: charlotte (beef casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onions and peppers with beef and drain.
In large bowl or casserole dish, combine soup, ketchup, Worcestershire
and noodles.
Stir in tomatoes and meat. Spread in casserole dish.
Garnish with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candied sweet potatoes or carrots
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise, then cut like a French fry.
Wash potatoes and drain.
Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar; cook over medium heat.
Add wet potatoes, placing all in one direction.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top of potatoes.
Cover and cook until you hear steam inside pan.
Turn heat to low; cook for 10 minutes.
Use syrup mixture to baste over potatoes.
Repeat basting often.
Cook until tender, or about 15 minutes.

title: scalloped hash brown-cheese potato bake
directions: Thaw bag of frozen hash browns (about 2 hours).
Saute of chopped onion in melted butter.
Pour over hash browns and stir. Add sour cream and cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir in cream of celery soup and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch glass dish for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: homemade play dough(nonedible)
directions: Thoroughly mix together preceeding ingredients.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool slightly and knead thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container.
It lasts a long time and has a better texture than commercial play dough.
(You may add a few drops of oil of wintergreen or cinnamon to give a pleasant aroma, but only if the children understand it's not to eat!)

title: polynesian sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake uncovered for 3 hours at 250°.
Stir gently at end of 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: harvest fruit salad
directions: Cut and peel white membrane from oranges, holding oranges over bowl to catch juice; lift out sections.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of the juice.
In a large bowl, combine the orange sections, celery, grapes and raisins.
Cover and refrigerate until the next day.

title: rhubarb jell
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
Next morning, heat and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool, then add raspberry jello and strawberry jello.
Will keep indefinitely in freezer and 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: the golden girl's golden macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni 20 minutes; wash and drain.
Keep macaroni warm. Mix cheese into warm macaroni.
Melt margarine just a bit.
Pour over macaroni with the cheese in it.
Blend eggs and evaporated milk well.
Stir in with cheese and margarine.
(Leave about 1/3 of grated cheese to put on top of macaroni.)
Cover top of dish with leftover cheese.
Sprinkle a little paprika over the top for color.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in oven at 450°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in microwave.
Add hamburger last after cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
(Keep hot while serving.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour water over apples.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Measure flour, then sift flour, spices, salt and soda twice.
Add flour to sugar mixture.
Add apples and the water; mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together all but Hershey bar and chocolate chips after crushing the cereal.
Roll into balls and freeze.
Dip in mixture of Hershey bar and chocolate chips.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Place the squirrel in pot and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper and boil until meat is tender.
Remove pieces of meat and roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together.
In large bowl put a layer of crackers, strawberries and layer of cream cheese mixture, then repeat until bowl is full.

title: okra
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
remove bacon and cut okra in small circles and fry until most of sticky stuff is out.
Then add the tomatoes and onion and crumble the bacon into pan.
Serve warm. Cook only enough to heat tomatoes, simmer 20 minutes.

title: honey-marmalade nut bread
directions: Sift flour and baking powder, then set aside; beat honey, butter and eggs until smooth.
Stir in marmalade and orange peel; mix well and add flour.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour for loaf pan or 35 to 40 minutes for smaller pans.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease 13 x 9-inch pan. After hamburger is browned and drained, mix vegetables, soup, onion and milk.
Heat through.
Set aside.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in large pan, stirring constantly 5 minutes.
Add pecans and butter and cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Cool a few minutes.
Beat until loses gloss. Pour onto waxed paper rapidly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir dry soup into spinach thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Chill and serve with baked corn chips, pita chips, raw vegetables and crackers, etc.

title: eunice's pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and bake in 9 x 13 pan. Boil pineapple & sugar until sugar is dissolved. Poke holes in warm cake, pour pineapple over cake and let sit until cool. Spread Cool Whip over cake, sprinkle nuts and coconut over cake. Refrigerate.

title: nut-capped baked apples
directions: Core apples; pare upper third of each apple to prevent skin from splitting.
Place apples upright in ungreased baking pan. Mix raisins, honey and 2 tablespoons chopped pecans.
Fill center of each apple with raisin mixture.
Pour hot water into pan to 1/4-inch depth.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool apples 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon topping onto apples and sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Serve warm or cold.

title: casserole onion bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to warm. Combine in bowl, cottage cheese, sugar, instant onion, butter, dill weed, salt, baking soda, eggs and yeast.
Add flour to form stiff dough (stir with spoon).
Cover and leave in bowl; let rise until double in size.

title: fruited chicken macaroni salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion and salt.
Cook macaroni; rinse and chill.
Add celery, fruit and nuts to chicken.
Stir in macaroni. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and lemon juice (these may need to be increased).
Halve or cut up cantaloupe.
Serve salad in or over cantaloupe; use lettuce for a bed.

title: orange eggnog
directions: Blend all ingredients on high speed for 5 to 10 seconds. Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Fry bacon well done.
Take out of skillet and place on paper towel.
Cook potatoes well done.
Drain off water.
Chop onion up fine.
Add to the potatoes.
Add the vinegar, sugar and pepper to taste.
Add however much mustard you would like.
Crush bacon up fine.
Add to the potatoes.
Mix well and serve.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press mixture in bottom and sides of a spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, lemon juice and rind.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Release sides on pan. Serves 10 to 12.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to boil and cook slow for 1 hour. Serve hot with cornbread.

title: fruit salad
directions: First:
Cook pudding according to directions on package.
Set aside to cool.
May put in refrigerator.

title: banana split
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and margarine together in bottom of large dish; pack.
Slice bananas and put over crumbs, then add pineapple.
Beat eggs with sugar and pour over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip; top with nuts and cherries.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and season hamburger to taste.
In large bowl combine lettuce, cheese, kidney beans, tomatoes and taco chips (crushed). Add cooked hamburger and French dressing and toss.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy, in large mixer bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with kisses.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°, until cookie cracks.

title: creamy ice dessert(frozen fassion)
directions: Pour milk and soda pop into the freeze drum of the ice cream freezer and let the freezer do the rest.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: peanut butter ho-ho cake
directions: Cream together crisco, butter and sugar.
Add flour, milk and peanut butter.
Chill mixture.

title: white and black bean salad
directions: Saut onions and garlic in oil until crisp-tender in medium skillet; remove from heat and cool until warm.
Stir vinegar, peppers, parsley, Equal, salt and pepper into onions.
Pour onion mixture over combined beans in a bowl; mix well.
Garnish with pepper rings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil noodles.
Chop onions and eggs.
Devein shrimp; rinse and drain.
Chop shrimp.
Add chopped ingredients to cooked shell noodles that have been rinsed and drained with cold water (to prevent sticking).
Add seasonings.
Slowly add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Do not add too much mayonnaise or it will become "runny".
You have to use Kraft real mayonnaise to achieve proper flavor, however, you may use light brand.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients; form into a ball and roll the ball into chopped nuts.
Cover all the cheese; keep cold.
Store in refrigerator.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick; add water.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold into egg/sugar mixture.
Pour into shallow pan lined with waxed paper.
Spread thinly.
Bake about 12 minutes in 400° oven.
Invert onto cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Spread with warmed jelly or jam and roll quickly.

title: pasta frittata pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a round glass pan or a pie pan. Beat the eggs until well mixed in a large bowl.
Stir in the remaining ingredients except butter including any optional additions.
Pour the mixture into the buttered pan.
Cut the butter into bits and distribute across top of mixture.
Place in oven and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and mix very lightly. Return to oven and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out almost dry.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Good with a salad and crusty fresh rolls.

title: venison jerky
directions: If it grows beneath the ground (root vegetables), it grows in the cold earth; then start it in cold water and cover the pot with a lid.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk, 1 cup flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder and pinch of salt. Pour into butter.
Pour 3 cups sweetened fruit on top of all this. When baked, crust will be on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet, cook chicken and vegetables, stirring constantly for 5 minutes or until chicken is almost done.
Add cup of soup.
Blend well with water and bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot vermicelli.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fried fresh corn
directions: Heat grease in skillet on medium heat.
Add corn, flour, meal and salt.
Cover with water.
Cut butter up into corn.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent sticking, until corn is done.

title: fish stew
directions: In skillet combine bouillon, water, garlic and catsup.
Add vegetables and top with fish and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: chocolate fudgie fig cookies(yields 475 to 500 cookies)
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add flavoring and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times; add to creamed mixture.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet with a #40 scoop.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: low calorie orange mandarin cake delight
directions: *Prepare as package directs.

title: green chicken curry
directions: Heat the oil in a wok or large, heavy frying pan. Add the onion and curry paste to the wok and cook for one minute, stirring constantly. Add the coconut milk and water to the wok and bring to a boil. Add the chicken pieces, beans, and lime leaves to the wok, stirring to combine. Reduce the heat and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the chicken is tender. Do not overcook. Add the fish sauce, lime juice, lime rind, and sugar to the wok; stir to combine. Sprinkle with fresh cilantro just before serving. Serve with steamed rice. Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into loaf.
Wrap bacon around loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or use Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and spread.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May add sliced pepperoni if like.
Serve warm.
Good for brunches or potluck suppers.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Remove approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops; pour off fat.
Place chops in baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place slice of onion and pepper ring on each; pour soup over.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: corn balls
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter.
Cool.
Mix in with other ingredients.
Shape into 8 or 10 balls.
Place in ungreased shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fill 6 pie plates with rock salt and place oyster on half shell on rock salt.
Heat 1/4 c/ butter in a pan and add minced green onion.
Stir in parsley, bread crumbs, spinach, Pernod, celery powder, lemon juice and cayenne pepper. Add remaining butter and mix well.
Spoon mixture by tsps. onto oysters and top with bacon pieces.
Bake in oven 8-10 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Serve immediately in pan of rock salt. Champagne goes great with this. Serves 4.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put beans in casserole dish. Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning as directed on seasoning package. Add this to top of beans in dish.
Spread salsa on top of meat. Add cheese (save a little to sprinkle on top).
Microwave until cheese melts. After removing from microwave spread with sour cream. Top with olives, chopped green onions and diced tomatoes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Serve warm with chips.

title: chili dip
directions: In a microwave safe dish pour in the Armour chili.
Then cut up and spread cream cheese on the top of chili.
Last spread shredded cheese around the top.
Place in microwave until shredded cheese is melted and dish is warm all through.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in sealed jars.
Measure 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to one cup of boiling water.
Use this as a gift idea for teachers, close friends or neighbors.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix crushed wafers, sugar and melted butter; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate.
Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar and half container of Cool Whip; spread on first layer.
Mix lemon instant pudding and milk according to package directions. Spread on second layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean.
Combine mushroom stems (chopped fine), salt, pepper, cream cheese and dill.
Process until smooth.
Pack into clean mushroom caps.
Place on a cookie sheet and broil lightly until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: steak picatta
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add onion and saute until onion is transparent (2 to 3 minutes).
Add all of remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to low.
Simmer.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: In
place of Veg-All you may want to add cooked broccoli, cauliflower
and water chestnuts.
Melt above ingredients over very low heat.

title: super snack mix
directions: Melt together butter, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add to cereal; coat well.
Spread into jelly roll pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Add pretzels and M&M's; mix.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: For a large bowl of fresh fruit, recipe may be doubled.
This dip goes with watermelon, cantaloupe, grapes, strawberries, honeydew, bananas, cherries, apples, oranges, peaches or any fresh fruit.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In saucepan, place chicken, soup, water and onion.
Heat.
In casserole or baking dish, place about 3 tablespoons meat-soup mixture.
Tear tortillas and place 1 layer over chicken mixture. Top with cheese.
Layer until all meat mixture is used.
Top with cheese and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes until heated through and cheese has melted.

title: ntozake chicken
directions: Rub chicken with garlic.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Roll chicken parts in butter.
(Turn skin side up.)
Dust with cinnamon.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Sprinkle with wine and sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Frozen potatoes don't have to be thawed.
Just break up potatoes and add all the ingredients.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8. Can be prepared in afternoon for a dinner party.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla, eggs and melted butter; blend well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Turn mixture into pie shells.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set around edge of pies.
Makes 2 pies, 6 to 8 servings each.

title: fiesta
directions: Prepare ahead of time and serve in numbered bowls, buffet style.
Arrange on your plate according to number.
Dig in! Guests may follow the order or "skip" those they don't want.

title: russian snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour and salt; add to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet. Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 20 minutes.
Do not brown. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: manhattan apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water. Add vinegar and salt. Pour thin layer in mold; chill until firm. Combine apples and celery; place in mold. Add remaining gelatin.
Chill until firm. Unmold on crisp lettuce.
Yields 8 servings.

title: weldon's shrimp creole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients, then add the next 10 ingredients. Cook on low for 7 hours. You can put the crab boil in for extra "heat" and let it stay in 15 to 20 minutes. Add 6 to 7 pounds fresh or frozen shrimp. Continue simmering until the shrimp is done; remove bay leaves and shrimp boil and serve over rice.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Shell and devein the shrimp.
In a large skillet with heatproof handle, heat butter and olive oil.
Saute garlic until golden, about 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook just until pink.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with parsley and bread crumbs.
Place under broiler and broil 2 to 3 minutes until crumbs are golden brown.
Serve garnished with lemon wedges.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Add partially thawed berries and juice.
Thicken some, pour over cream cheese layer and refrigerate until set.

title: barbra's enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, chilies, 4 cups shredded cheeses, olives, 1/2 cup onions and chicken in bowl.
Place a portion of filling across each tortilla and roll like jelly roll.
Place side by side in sprayed baking dish.
Spread remaining sauce mix over top of enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining grated cheeses and green onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carbonnades flamanndes(flemish beef stew)
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in 1/2 butter in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup more flour over meat, mix well. In a separate skillet, saute garlic, onions and butter remaining. Combine meat in large casserole.
Add remaining ingredients except vinegar.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add vinegar shortly before serving with noodles or rice.
Can be cooked in Dutch oven on top of stove, covered.

title: lime yogurt pie(8 servings)
directions: In bowl, combine gelatin powder and yogurt. Fold in whipped topping. Spread into crust. Refrigerate at least 20 minutes.

title: clandestine dip(a delicious salsa)
directions: Mix ingredients (the same day).
Let stand for several hours in the refrigerator.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter the baking dish.
Mix oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add melted butter to oatmeal mixture and mix with fork until well blended.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Put sliced apples in buttered baking dish. Spread oatmeal mixture on top of apples.
Bake approximately 35 minutes.

title: sausage and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cut the sausage in small pieces.
Brown in Dutch oven.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cheez whiz casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onions and celery.
Cook noodles and drain. Add all other ingredients to meat mixture and bake for 45 minutes covered at 350°.

title: rodeo hash
directions: In skillet, brown beef in shortening with potatoes and celery, stirring to separate meat. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir often.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Stir in.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies fluff up at first, then flatten out.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hamburger cobbler
directions: Throw first 5 ingredients into pan and brown in a teaspoon of oil.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add 6 slices of pimento cheese.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Throw over top of cheese.
Place 10 biscuits on top of it all.
Cook in oven at 425° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in orange juice and orange peel, shortening and egg to dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in cranberries and chopped nuts.
Turn into a two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans, greased on bottom only.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes two loaves.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes, then bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; beat.
Sift brown sugar in the bottom of a loaf pan.
Gently pour custard over sugar.
Place in a shallow baking pan containing hot water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Do not cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, run a knife around edge of pan.
Turn out onto a small platter.

title: golden potato medley
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes, slice carrots, cover with boiling water, simmer until vegetables are tender; drain.
Melt butter in pan. Add onions and green pepper.
Saute until onion is tender; blend in flour and add milk.
Cook until all blended in.
Remove from heat, add pimientos and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese until blended

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer a while.
Serve over hot cornbread.

title: mother-n-law's cole slaw
directions: Peel and wash vegetables.
Dry and run through meat grinder or food processor to chop fine.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.
Better if sets overnight.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, red and green pepper, mustard and salt.
Add crabmeat, being careful not to shred. Divide into 4 baking shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in an ungreased shallow baking pan. With wet hands, shape into loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Steam peppers 5 to 7 minutes. Slice the
tops
off
and
scoop	the centers out.
Saute the onions and ground beef in the butter until the meat is brown. Add	the rice, eggs and seasonings.	Fill the steamed peppers; stand
them in	a
buttered baking dish and sprinkle Parmesan cheese
on
top of each.
Bake for 10 minutes or put under the broiler until bubbling.
Serves 4.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix punch, pineapple juice and ginger ale together.
Add sherbet to mixture by scoops when ready to serve.

title: microwave pumpkin pie
directions: Break eggs into 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Beat lightly.
Add pumpkin and remaining ingredients, adding one at a time, mixing well. Pour mixture into pie shell.
Place in microwave oven.
Cook 18 minutes or until almost set; let stand 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: creamy italian toss
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix mayo, vinegar, mustard, onion and pepper together.
Mix other ingredients together and toss. Chill several hours and serve.

title: shanghai sauce
directions: Prepare chicken wings as usual and fry in oil until done.

title: sauce for sausage
directions: Cook about 10 minutes.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Mix well; chill overnight.

title: cheesy turkey casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 12-inch or larger pan.
Layer turkey on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over turkey.
Spread broccoli over cheese.
Salt to taste.
Add up to 1/2 portion of gravy, not too thick.
Make sure gravy is warm.
Add hot Mexican Velveeta cheese. Add remaining gravy portion on top of cheese, warm, not too thick.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or longer if needed to melt cheese.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In 2 to 3-quart casserole, spray with Pam.
Layer 1/2 can tomato soup.
Top with 1/2 chopped cabbage.
Mix rice, meat, onion, garlic, spices and 1 can tomato soup.
Layer meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Top with remaining cabbage and cover with remaining soup.
Bake at 350° until meat is done.
Cover dish for juicier cabbage.

title: southern pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Pour over chops.
Add rice and salt. Add vegetables; top with pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Serves 4.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Crumble bacon and combine with remaining ingredients, except chili powder.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into ball on wax paper. Sprinkle with chili powder and cover ball evenly.
Wrap and chill thoroughly.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter (use medium size pot) until tender.
Add chicken broth, pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Cover pot and reduce heat.
Simmer until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pork chops and potato scallop
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix soup, sour cream, water and parsley. Layer potatoes, onions and sauce mixture in casserole.
Top with pork chops.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna fish pie
directions: Cover with crust and bake at 350° in oven until brown.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place breast halves between sheets of wax paper; pound with mallet.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken on high heat (4 minutes on each side); remove from pan.
Add chives or green onions, lime or lemon, brandy or cognac, parsley and mustard to the pan.
Cook for 15 minutes, whisking constantly.
Whisk in chicken broth; stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately, with noodles or rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the apples, sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl; let stand for an hour.
Stir often so that the mixture makes its own juice. Combine dry ingredients and add to apples.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Do not use a mixer.
Stir ingredients together by hand. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add carrots and nuts; beat well.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: garam masala(spice mixture necessary for keema mattar and chicken tikka.)
directions: In a small pan, roast separately the coriander, cumin, peppercorns, cardamon, cinnamon and cloves.
As each one begins to smell fragrant, turn onto a plate to cool.
Put all ingredients in a blender and grind to a fine powder.
Add nutmeg.
Store in airtight container.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Let the cukes, onions and salt stand for 3 hours; do not drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Do not heat; mix well. Put in 1-gallon covered containers.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put into a 2-quart casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°. Just before you take it out of the oven, cover with chow mein noodles or a can of onion rings and bake another 10 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: With mixer or blender, beat eggs.
Mix flour, sugar and butter. Beat into eggs.
Add almond extract.
Peel peaches and slice into pie crust until level with top of crust.
Pour mixture over peaches and bake in middle of oven 10 minutes at 400°, then 50 minutes at 350° or until firmly set and lightly brown on top.

title: era's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa powder and salt together.
Add water. Mix thoroughly and cook on low heat until simmering.
Increase heat until it comes to a rolling boil.
The mixture will thicken when cooled.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: spicy tomato-artichoke sauce over pasta *
directions: Peel, seed (squeezing out excess juice) and chop tomatoes. Drain artichokes and reserve marinade.
Heat olive oil in large saucepan and saute onions, garlic, basil, oregano, parsley and red pepper flakes over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Crush peppercorns and add to onion mixture.
Add tomatoes to sauce; season with about 1 teaspoon salt and simmer, uncovered, over medium heat 1 hour.
Add reserved artichoke marinade and simmer, stirring often, another 30 minutes.
Stir in artichokes and continue to simmer until sauce is thick, about 20 minutes more.
Stir in Romano cheese.

title: dirty brown rice
directions: Pour rice in casserole dish.
Add chopped onion.
Pour beef broth over mixture.
Slice margarine or butter into small pieces and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Frost.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Drain oysters,	reserving
liquid.
Saute
onion, green pepper, celery and	garlic	in
butter
in large skillet until lightly browned.
Add okra, tomatoes, broth, oyster liquid and seasoning.	Cover
and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes.
Then add oysters and cook 1 minute.
Remove
bay leaf.	Meanwhile, combine water and 1/2 teaspoon
salt
and rice.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Remove from heat;
let	stand
minutes.
To serve, spoon rice into soup bowls; ladle gumbo over rice.

title: beef "n" casserole
directions: *May also use steaks, chunked.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut butter into flour and sugar with a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Press into pan evenly and firmly, using fingertips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: aunt jan's banana bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift in flour and soda, alternating with stirring in buttermilk and bananas.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan; bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Pour off fat.
Stir in 2 cups tomato juice, tomato paste, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: yellow rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice according to directions on package.
Heat Mexicorn and shredded cheese.
Mix cheese soup, corn (drained) and rice together in casserole dish.
Heat casserole in oven until cheese melts and it is warm all the way through.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt together. Set aside.
Cream shortening; add sugar, pumpkin and egg.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: delicious rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add rice and raisins, if desired, and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into 1-inch balls and brown over medium heat in a large, deep skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Remove all grease from skillet.
Add catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and water.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add pineapple chunks.
Simmer, covered, until heated thoroughly. Serves 6.

title: spicy ravioli salad
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Drain ravioli; stir into tomato mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: trash
directions: In shallow pan, melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together until all ingredients are well coated. Bake in 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: potato skin snack
directions: Scrub potatoes and coat with cooking spray; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell. (Pulp may be reserved for other uses.)
Cut shells into 5 (1/2-inch wide) strips.
Place strips skin side down on a baking sheet.
Brush with dressing; sprinkle with seasoning blend.
Broil 6 inches from heat 5 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm. Yield: 20 appetizers (11 calories each).

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into 1 inch cubes.
Place cheese in large, microwave safe glass bowl.
Add 1/3 to 1/2 c. milk.
Microwave on medium setting for about 10 minutes (stirring every 2 minutes) until melted.
If you need to thin the mixture more, add milk and stir.
Finely chop peppers until you have about 3 tablespoons. Add to cheese.
Microwave 1 minute, stir well.
If you want the cheese dip to be more spicy, add jalapeno juice from the jar 1 Tbsp at a time.

title: pineapple thick shake
directions: In blender container combine milk, pineapple, extract and, if desired, sugar substitute.
Process until smooth.
Makes 1 serving.

title: creamy beef stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Stir in flour and salt until well blended. Stir in soup, consomme and mustard. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir in noodles and sour cream. Heat through (do not boil). Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook together the ground beef, bacon and onion until no longer pink;
drain.
Stir
together
the brown sugar, catsup and vinegar and add to the meat mixture.
Slightly drain the 4 cans of beans and add to other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave, covered, for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: double crust pizza casserole
directions: For crust, combine flour, potatoes, milk and butter.
Set aside.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 large loaf for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or 2 small loaves for 50 minutes at 350°, or bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "grandma's" carrot cookies
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in mashed carrots.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; blend into batter.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.
Cool; ice.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray a baking dish with cooking spray. Dip the chicken in the melted margarine. Combine remaining ingredients and coat the chicken with the crumb mixture. Place in a baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: texas salad
directions: Combine lettuce, tomatoes, onions, beans and cheese.
Sprinkle heavily all over top with chili powder.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours. At the last minute, add crushed corn chips and salad dressing.
Mix.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Spray a large Bundt pan with Pam.
Put rolls in pan and sprinkle other ingredients over the top.
Let set overnight in uncovered pan.
In the morning, bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Invert on large plate.
Serves 12.
Easy recipe for kids.

title: spud soup
directions: Peel and chunk potatoes.
Cook with 5 cups water until done. Add cream of broccoli soup and 1 can of milk.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes and serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple-jello salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and Jell-O in a microwave-safe bowl. Let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together with a large spoon.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: 7 layer magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch dish or pan, melt margarine or butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Press firmly in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Fry slowly in oil until browned. Serves 6.

title: rose audrey patton's custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar-free tang salad
directions: Mix 1 small tub of sugar-free Tang (dry) and pudding.
Add chunk pineapple in its own juice, including the juice.
Drain 2 small cans of mandarin oranges and add.
Drain several maraschino cherries and cut in half.
Add for color.
Refrigerate and let salad set overnight for best taste.
Before serving, add 4 to 6 sliced bananas.

title: selma's salad
directions: Boil can of tomato soup; add cheese and beat until creamy. Cool and add salad dressing, gelatine and remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix together soups and water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: nana's coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Heat juices to simmer stage. Pour over Jell-O.
Cool and add Coke, chopped cherries, cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: cranberry layered salad
directions: Dissolve two packages of Jello with 2 cups of hot water.
Add can of crushed pineapple and can of WHOLE cranberry sauce.
Stir and mash with a fork.
Add chopped nuts; stir to spread evenly. Pour into a 9 x 13 glass pan or plastic container.
Refrigerate to set and chill.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Cook macaroni in water with salt; drain and add 1/2 teaspoon salt, meat and remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Mushrooms may be added if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ground beef pot pie
directions: Saute ground sirloin, onion and garlic in non-stick skillet. Add celery, peas, carrots, 1 can of tomato sauce, salt and worcestershire sauce; simmer 15 minutes. Pour mixture into casserole dish. Arrange eight of the biscuits around the edge of the dish. Sprinkle grated cheese over the top of the biscuits. Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over the biscuits and casserole. Bake in 400 degree oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until biscuits are lightly golden.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Bring to boil marshmallows and 7-Up.
Dump in cream cheese and Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Let cool.
Then fold in Cool Whip.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and Cool Whip together in large bowl.
Pour into graham pie crust and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine flour, shortening, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Mix as for pie crust.
Pour egg yolk into cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Stir the milk mixture into dough.
Roll out half the dough; set on a large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cornflakes over dough.
Place apples over cornflakes.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
(Butter over the top of the apples, optional.) Roll out remaining dough.
Place over apples for top crust.
Pinch edges together firmly.
Beat egg white until stiff; brush over top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Combine powdered sugar and enough water to make of spreading consistency; spread evenly over hot pastry.
Yields 24 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and 1 cup of sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine with apples.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: save a penny casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain.
Stir in the soup, spaghetti and vegetables.
Pour into ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, sprinkle with cheese and let stand until melted.
Serve. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend
all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in a large
mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed with an electric
mixer.
Pour
batter
into
greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed or pulls away from the side of pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted, boiling water until tender.
Drain well.
Brown the ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Add milk, catsup, cheese and soup with the beef and macaroni.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle additional cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot and golden brown.

title: ham and split pea soup
directions: In large stockpot, bring water, split peas, carrots, mushrooms, ham, garlic and bouillon cubes to boil. Reduce to simmer for 1 hour or until peas are tender. Add spices to taste.

title: summer stew
directions: Chop vegetables into bite size pieces. Place all ingredients in heavy skillet and cook slow. You may want to boil potatoes a little before adding to the stew.

title: baklava
directions: Butter bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Lay 10 sheets of phyllo in pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Mix nuts with sugar and spices, sprinkle 1/2 over phyllo.

Drizzle with melted butter. Lay on another 10 sheets of phyllo, brushing each with butter. Sprinkle with other half of nut mixture, add remaining phyllo, cut without cutting through bottom layer in diamond-shaped pieces. Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Finish cutting.
Allow to cool.
Pour warm Lemon Honey Syrup over.
Makes about 20.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil on low heat.
Add all ingredients; bring to a bubble and then reduce heat to simmer for 1 hour.
Add hot Italian sausage for added flavor.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix in flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Process on low for 30 seconds in blender.
Chill.

title: cranberry fruit-nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Combine orange juice and grated rind with well beaten egg. Pour all at once into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen. Carefully fold in chopped nuts and cranberries. Spoon into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch or several small loaf pans). Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, about 1 hour (time varies with smaller pans) until crust is golden brown and toothpick comes out clean. Remove from pan. Cool. Store overnight for easy slicing.

title: cinnamon frosted zucchini bars
directions: Generously grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Set aside. In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together (except pecans). Form into ball. Chill 1 hour, then roll in pecans.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Cool eggs in cold water for 10 minutes.
Peel eggs and cut lengthwise.
With egg yolks, add salad dressing, mustard and salt.
Mix well until creamy.
Fill egg whites with mixture.

title: potato logs
directions: Scrub potatoes very good and slice into 8 wedges.
Cover with boiling water and cook until tender.
Remove from water and place onto a shallow baking sheet.
Spray potatoes with Pam.
Sprinkle seasoning over potatoes, use the amount that is suitable for your families' taste.
Turn oven on broil, place potatoes in oven until slightly brown.
Serve hot.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: cheesy chivey potato casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Grate potatoes or cut in chunks. In a pan over low heat, combine butter and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and stir in salt, pepper, sour cream and onions.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir lightly and turn into prepared casserole.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add liquids and beat well.
Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.
Pour coffee cans half full of batter and bake at 350°, about 50 minutes.
Let cool and remove from cans.

title: fork cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening, then add eggs.
Beat well.
Add soda and cream of tartar.
Sift together with flour.
Then add salt and vanilla.
From a tablespoon of dough form a ball and place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake in 400° oven until the cookies are brown.
Makes about 70 cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the cheese, soup, onion, pepper and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add potatoes to the mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until casserole is browned.

title: spicy nut triangles
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk; beat well. Sift flour and cinnamon together. Gradually add to creamed mixture and stir well. Spread dough in a jelly roll pan, 12 x 15-inches. Beat egg white slightly.
Brush over top.
Smooth with fingertips. Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Stir together in a one gallon jar (glass).
Stir every day. Keep lid on or cover loosely.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and next 5 ingredients and add all together.
Bake in well-greased muffin pan (12) in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until browned and done.

title: shrimp potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt and soup.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 of the Tater Tots.
Add all of the meat mixture.
Cover with remaining Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese on top.
Melt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix, soups, broth and butter together.
Put half of mixture into prepared casserole dish.
Cover with chicken and pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Blend and turn into 13 x 9-inch metal pan that has been greased or sprayed and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
In a glass dish bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chex bars
directions: Stir the first 2 ingredients in a 3-quart pan over medium heat until it boils. Take off heat; add peanut butter and mix well. Add Crispix and peanuts.
Mix.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Blend all but cheese.
Use glass loaf pan or line with aluminum foil.
Divide meat mixture into 2 layers, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 meat and 1/2 cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Let it stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Add food coloring (different color for each batch).
Cook three minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Mixture forms a ball when done. Knead dough on wax paper.
Store in airtight containers in refrigerator.

title: preserves using any kind of fruit
directions: Mix fruit and 1 1/2 cups sugar well.
Start on medium heat; keep stirring.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes, not a hard boil.
Remove from heat; add 1 cup sugar and put back on heat and boil for 10 minutes more.
Remove from heat and put into jars.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Blend until smooth in large mixing bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients to liquid ingredients. Mix for 15 minutes at regular speed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in an ungreased angel food pan.
Do not ice.
Powder sugar if wished.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dried chipped beef together.
Add garlic salt.
Roll in a ball.
Cover with chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: new baby chicken(easy to prepare - good dish to bring to the "new mom")
directions: Arrange chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place a slice of cheese on each breast.
Top with mushrooms.
Mix soup and wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing on top, then drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Combine sugars, syrup, margarine, vanilla and 1 cup milk in large saucepan.
Stir well and bring to boil, stirring constantly; add remaining cup of milk slowly without stopping the boiling. Cook to soft ball stage; add pecans and pour into a large buttered pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water.
Dip squares into chocolate and place to cool on waxed paper.

title: coconut almond carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed with mixer until mixed well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg. Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup of coconut.
Pour in greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool.

title: sausage and egg souffle
directions: Crumble and slightly brown sausage and drain off fat.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir well.
Add cheese and sausage.
Pour mixture into a Pyrex dish (8 x 12-inch) and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: skillet supper
directions: I slice my potatoes and put in a big skillet; fry them up not completely done.
Add chopped onion and hot dogs, then fry a little longer.
Scramble up your eggs and then pour over your potatoes and cook until done.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heap cabbage in bowl.
Combine cream, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage and toss lightly.
Arrange eggs around rim of bowl for trim. Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled swordfish
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate fish 1 to 3 hours.
Grill 8 minutes per slice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cake(a stand-by for years)
directions: Cream fat with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg; blend well. Dissolve soda in warm pumpkin or other selection.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Last, add raisins and nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into 1-inch balls. Bake in a 400° oven until light golden brown.

title: sensibly delicious chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Cream brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until centers are set.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Fix cake according to directions.
Let cool.
Cut into 4 equal parts.
Fix pudding according to directions.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form into a ball. Top with paprika for color or roll in pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: good sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pickle. Then add ketchup, mustard, brown sugar and mushroom soup.
Simmer for 15 minutes and serve.

title: vanilla cream caramels
directions: You must have a heavy pan.
In order not to be caught short, have everything ready before you start: thermometer, spoon, buttered pan (two 6 x 12-inch or equivalent).

title: cranberried squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly oil large baking dish. Cut each squash in half; remove seed. Place squash in baking dish, cut side up. Combine all remaining ingredients; spoon equally into the squash "cups". Bake until filling bubbles and squash is soft, about 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool slightly before serving. Serves 4.

title: ramps cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients into iron skillet and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry delight cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package, remembering to add the fourth egg.
Allow layers to cool.
Then cut layers in half, giving you 4 thin layers.
(Use thread or dental floss.)
Cream the cream cheese; add powdered sugar and Cool Whip mixing until thoroughly combined.
Starting with first layer, frost top with cream cheese mixture, then small amount of pie filling.
Repeat until all layers are stacked.
Remember to frost only the top of each layer, not the sides.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts to dry ingredients. Beat egg and mix with milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and stir only until dry mixture is moistened.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all together on high of electric blender until ice is almost liquified.
Makes 6 small servings.

title: cream cheese party mold
directions: Cream the Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add sour cream, sugar, gelatine and raisins; mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
When ready to serve, decorate mold with almonds.
Serve with crackers.
This cream cheese mold freezes very well and can be thawed and used later.

title: coke cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Bring to boil the Coke, cocoa and butter.
Pour into flour mixture and stir well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to other mixture.
Add eggs; stir in marshmallows.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: sharp vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve over fresh salad.

title: cheese and potato pie
directions: Prepare the potatoes as usual.
Grate the cheese and add to the potatoes; mix well.
Place in an ovenproof dish and cook in a moderate oven for about 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake 2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan; set aside. In medium bowl, combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
In large mixing bowl, beat oil and sugars until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients and continue mixing until well combined.
Fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake for 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Combine
and
mix
well all ingredients except peas and white sauce.
Pack
into well-buttered ring mold.
Place mold in
larger pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Stir peas
into white
sauce.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes. Invert
carrot loaf onto serving plate.
Spoon creamed peas in center.
Serve remaining sauce on the side.

title: spinach noodles
directions: Cook, drain and puree spinach in the blender.
Combine spinach puree, egg and salt.
Stir in gradually the flour, then knead until smooth.
Place dough in covered container for 30 minutes. Roll out very thin on floured surface.
Let this dry some, not too dry to roll up.
Roll up and cut into very thin strips.
Toss apart and let dry throughly.
Store in airtight container or let dry at least 2 hours and cook, uncovered, 10 minutes in boiling water.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg; add alternately with buttermilk
to the creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop
by
tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at
for
10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly and
move
to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: creamy cheesy potatoes
directions: Blend milk into cream cheese in medium saucepan over low heat. Stir in chives, onion and salt.
Add potatoes; stir carefully to coat.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: momma's no fool's pie
directions: Melt margarine at 450°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over melted margarine.
Add fruit of your choice (peaches, strawberries, cherries, etc.).
Let brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add all other ingredients to spaghetti.
Refrigerate.

title: fluffy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water in tightly covered saucepan about 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add evaporated milk, salt and pepper until fluffy and light.
Add more evaporated milk for softer mashed potatoes.
Serves 5.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Melt margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and food coloring.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add buttermilk.
Combine soda and vinegar.
Add all to batter. Beat well with mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans, one long or 2 square pans.
Use any kind of frosting, but I like White Cream Cheese.

title: wrapple bars
directions: Add 1/2 cup oil and 1/2 cup water to the cake mix.
Spread 1/2 the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Lay wrapples over the top on mixture; sprinkle 2 cups of chocolate chips over top of wrapples.
Spread the rest of the cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Do not overbake.
Makes 20 bars.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding and milk with mixer, then add sour cream and Cool Whip.
In a large bowl alternate layers of pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti following label directions; drain.
Place in a buttered 8-cup shallow baking dish.

While spaghetti cooks, saute onion in butter or margarine until soft in a large saucepan. Blend in the flour, instant chicken broth or bouillon cube, salt, dry mustard and pepper; cook, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk, then the liquid from the mushrooms plus enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and bubbles 3 minutes; stir in mushrooms and pimentos.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Mix ground beef and onion.
Cook until light brown and drain. Mix all other ingredients together except cheese.
Heat well. Line bottom of pan with Doritos and pour all ingredients over chips.
Top with cheese and place in oven until cheese melts.

title: steamed beer burgers(bart's burgers)
directions: Pat hamburger into small patties not much bigger than a silver dollar.

Brown patties in skillet on top of stove and set aside. Spray aluminum roasting pan with vegetable oil cooking spray. Spread all of the thinly sliced onions evenly over bottom of pan. Layer browned hamburger patties over onion layer.
Pour bottle of barbecue sauce and bottle of beer over onions and burgers.
Cover aluminum roasting pan with heavy duty foil.
Be sure to seal all edges.
Place sealed roasting pan with burgers on hot charcoal grill and cover grill with lid.
Let burgers steam for approximately 1 hour.
Place 2-4 burgers with onions on bun and enjoy!

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Boil hamburger (or brown).
Put in an ungreased baking dish. Add tomato soup mixed with water; pour over hamburger.
Drain mixed vegetables.
Pour over soup.
Put mashed potatoes on top. Add salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; then heat on medium until candy thermometer reaches 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and let cool. Break into small bite sized pieces.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix all together except oats.
Boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add oats; beat well and drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Grease not oil a 13 X 9 inch pan.
In a large bowl blend all cake ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 45-55 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: microwave hash brown potato bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart dish place frozen potatoes.
Cover.
Cook on High 8 minutes.
Add soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover.
Cook on High 14 to 16 minutes, stirring once during cooking time.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together broccoli, onion, bacon and raisins.
Make a topping of mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spiced cornish game hens
directions: Wash and dry hens, loosen skin from breasts by forcing fingers between flesh and skin, leaving skin attached to keel bone if possible.

title: squash casserole("big four" foods recipe contest 1970)
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Add all ingredients, except corn chips and soup.
Cook until tender, then add cheese soup. Place 1/2 of corn chips in casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of squash mixture.
Place other 1/2 of corn chips and add the remainder of squash mixture.
Bake in 325° oven until it bubbles, about 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bob's party punch
directions: Make an ice ring and chill all ingredients.
Place ice ring in punch bowl, open and add all ingredients to punch bowl.
This recipe can be cut in half for a small group.

title: cabbage wedges with cheese sauce
directions: Cut cabbage head into 6 wedges.
Cook in large pan of salted water until done or steam the wedges.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Save 2 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Add flour, salt, pepper and cayenne and blend well.
Add milk and water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add cheese until melted.
Drain cabbage and place on platter.
Pour sauce over wedges and sprinkle with bacon crumbs.

title: cheesy green bean pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Drain green beans, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. Combine green beans and reserved liquid with pasta, green onions, basil and garlic; heat through. Toss with cheese and serve immediately. Makes 4 servings. Prep time: 5 minutes. Cook time: 15 minutes.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in
boiling water; add lemon juice and cool. Cream together
cheese, sugar and vanilla.	Add gelatin and mix well.
Fold
in
whipped canned milk.
Combine cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Firmly
pack
2/3 of crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x
x
2-inch
pan.
Add
lemon	filling and sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine; stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half the mixture firmly onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: garbanzo patties
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together and stir.
Add enough corn flake crumbs to make a stiff mixture.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful equal to 1/4 cup into sprayed nonstick pan, using medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes on both sides.
Yields 10 patties. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Good served with spaghetti.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and 14 ounces of almond bark on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Continue to microwave for 1 to 2 minutes, until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with coconut.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Put in all vegetables plus basil and parsley.
Cook for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Then pour in tomato juice and tomato paste.
Add 1 large (46 ounces) can of water.
Simmer 5 hours, stirring every 20 minutes on low flame. Keep covered until it starts cooking good.
Add water as needed as it cooks.

title: quick chow mein
directions: In hot butter in large skillet, cook celery, green pepper and onion about 5 minutes.
Add sprouts, bouillon, soy sauce and meat, mixing until well combined.
Bring to boiling.
Remove from heat. Combine corn starch with 1 tablespoon cold water until smooth. Slowly stir into mixture.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini sausage casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender.
Mash lightly.
Add browned sausage, cut up bread, melted butter, seasoning and 1 cup cheese. Mix well.
Fold in eggs and pour into greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until brown and set.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Cool.
Add cranberry sauce; stir well.
Add pineapple and apples one at a time to prevent the apples from turning brown.
Add nuts; stir well. Refrigerate until set.

title: mini cheesecakes(serves 12)
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in cherries and juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
(Add red food coloring.) Cool.

title: snowballs(swedish)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in balls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
(Roll in hand.
If crumbles, it is not done.
Pick up and test.)
Once done, roll in powdered sugar twice, once when hot, once when cool.

title: calico beans
directions: In a frying pan, brown the bacon and onion.
Add catsup, sugar, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Stir to combine well.
Remove from heat and combine with beans.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove cover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: brown sugar peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, syrup, water and dash of salt.
Cook and stir until sugars dissolve.
When syrup boils, blend in butter.
Stir frequently after mixture reaches thread stage (230°).
Add peanuts when temperature reaches 280°.
Stir constantly until 300°.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve with taco chips.

title: breast of chicken scala
directions: Sprinkle chicken evenly with flour.
Melt the butter in a large skillet.
Saute chicken until brown on both sides, about 15 minutes.
Add soup; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, salt and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Remove chicken to a heatproof serving dish.
Stir sauce in pan to blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight in sauce to improve flavor, if desired.
Reheat.
Just before serving, sprinkle cheese over top and broil a minute or two until cheese is golden brown.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with frozen peas and grated cheese.
Crumble crisp bacon over top.
Seal and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: punch slush
directions: Mix until everything dissolves.
Pour into styrofoam cups, and place in freezer until frozen. Eat with a spoon.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Roll Oreo cookies in a storage bag until cookies are crumbly. Slightly thaw ice cream.
Put 1/4 cookies on bottom of 9x13-inch pan.
Mix together 1/2 of cookies crumbs, Cool Whip and ice cream. Spread over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs over the top and freeze.
Serve frozen.
I have also tried chocolate chip cookies with this recipe.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs,
milk
and
water and add sugar and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whipped topping
directions: Put ice water in a bowl.
Add non-fat dry milk to water. Beat water and nonfat dry milk until stiff.
Add sugar, a little at a time while beating.
Add lemon juice.
Beat until well mixed. Cover bowl and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: carrot snack cake
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until blended. Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in carrot.
In another bowl, combine flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to carrot mixture and stir until blended.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Place paper doily on top of the cake.
Lightly sift powdered sugar evenly over the doily, then carefully remove doily; 156 calories, 6 g. fat, 31 mg. cholesterol, 145 mg. sodium.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease but do not flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan, then sprinkle coconut over nuts.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Do not stir.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Melt butter, cocoa and water in a large pan.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Add to other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased and floured large bread pan. Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: macaroni antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients and add dressing.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter in top of a double boiler over boiling water; blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk, very slowly, stirring constantly.
This makes a smooth, thick white sauce.
Remove from heat; add grated cheese and stir until the cheese is melted. Separate the eggs.
Beat egg yolks and stir into the sauce.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold sauce gently into the egg whites.
Pour mixture into ungreased round, deep baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Then serve immediately.

title: ruby rhubarb salad
directions: In
saucepan,
combine	rhubarb,
sugar and water. Cook over medium
heat
for 3 minutes until tender.
Cool;
drain, reserving syrup.
Add
enough water to syrup to equal 2 cups. Return
and bring
to a boil. Stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Add
cup cold
water
and
lemon juice. When set, add rhubarb,
cream cheese and banana. Turn into 6 cup mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: delicious squash cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Boil squash and onion approximately 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and mash with fork. Add egg. Mix well. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Put into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake 50 minutes or until set.

title: grilled fish
directions: Preheat grill.
Place fish on sheet of aluminum foil. Spread melted margarine over fish, then sprinkle paprika on top. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add gelatin to boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
(Do not thaw.)
Add pineapple.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Grease an eight inch skillet and place in oven to heat. Beat egg in mixing bowl, add remaining ingredients, beat well. Pour batter into prepared skillet. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through cake with wooden spoon handle at 1-inch intervals.
Only after poking holes, combine pudding mix with sugar in large bowl; gradually stir in milk.
Then beat at low speed not more than 1 minute.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the cream cheese, egg, sugar, salt and chocolate chips.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with mix. Save some for top.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip Dream Whip and milk and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread half over crumbs and top with pie filling.
Add remaining cheese mixture and top with crumbs.
Chill well.

title: homemade apple butter
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and bake in an uncovered stainless steel roaster pan until the thickness desired, about 2 hours at 325°.
Stir about every 30 minutes.
Can the butter in hot, scalded jars and hot pack 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Then form in small balls. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lady bird's pecan pie
directions: Prepare the pie shell, folding overhang of pie crust under. Press about 18 pecan halves into pie crust edge at 1/2-inch intervals.
With floured, 4 tined fork, press edge of pie crust to pie plate between every 2 pecan halves.
Refrigerate.
Start heating oven to 325°.
In saucepan, combine the sugar, salt and corn syrup; simmer until sugar dissolves.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Mix well.
Put in large Pyrex dish and freeze.

title: salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl or serving dish. Serve with crackers.

title: kathleen's beer bread
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Put in cold oven.
Turn oven to 400°. Check in 45 minutes.
If browning too much on top, cover with foil. Should be ready in 60 minutes.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Bake cake.
Make your Jell-O following Jell-O directions. While cake is warm, pour Jell-O over cake after punching holes in the cake with a fork.
Chill.

title: easiest peach pie
directions: Mix peaches, tapioca and sugar.
Add lemon juice or Fruit-Fresh. (This mixture can be frozen at this point for later use.)
Place peach mixture in pie pan or baking dish.

title: margaret's macaroni salad(prep: 25 minutes; cook: 10 minutes; chill: 2 hours; serves 6)
directions: Cook macaroni in a large pot of rapidly boiling salted water until tender but still firm, about 10 minutes.
