Drain in a colander and rinse under cold running water.
Drain well.

title: joe's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Immerse fully cooked chicken in sauce and boil for approximately 5 minutes.

title: seafood pilaf
directions: In skillet brown rice in butter.
Add mushrooms, with liquid, remaining ingredients and 1/4 cup water.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 55 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Bake uncovered 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: renae's lasagna
directions: In skillet saute beef until brown.
Drain and season with salt and pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook lasagna noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and separate noodles.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Return 4 tablespoons fat to skillet.
Add flour, salt, celery and onion; cook gently.
Add sugar, vinegar, water and pepper; bring to a boil.	Add potatoes and diced bacon.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix well and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Knead for a few minutes.
Stretch and pat dough onto cookie sheet.
Dough may resist but eventually will relax.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
Pat and stretch over sides (will shrink back a bit).
Brush dough with olive oil.
Press garlic cloves and spread over dough.
Sprinkle Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese over dough.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cut into long strips and serve with pizza sauce for dipping.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 400° until done and browned off.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and beat about 3 minutes. Pour in greased 9 x 13 oblong pan or bake in 3 round cake pans. Bake at 325° until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and pour into greased casserole.

title: good and gooey bars
directions: Flour and grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the milk and caramels over low heat, stirring constantly.
Set aside.

title: easy one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Spread into greased 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Prepare beef and trim off excess fat.
Place beef in water in large Dutch oven.
Pare rutabaga, cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Remove 1/2-inch strip skin from around center of potatoes.
Pare parsnips, cut diagonally into 1-inch thick slices.
Pare carrots, cut in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 3-inch lengths.
Cut cabbage into wedges.
Add rutabaga to beef; simmer 10 minutes. Add onions; simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, parsnips and carrots; cover and simmer another 25 minutes.
After potatoes and other vegetables have simmered, add cabbage to beef.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Remove beef and slice brisket.
Serve with hot broth.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Brown onions in salad oil.
Mix the other ingredients and simmer in the same pan for 15 minutes.
Split the hot dogs and put in the sauce.
Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve on hot dog rolls.

title: easy beef stir-fry
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet. Combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard. Add to meat, then vegetables. Cover and simmer, stirring often until desired doneness. Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: ham ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add Ranch dressing. Stir in ham, cut in small bits. Spread in dish. Put crushed nuts on top or stir in.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together the ground beef, milk and seasonings. Separate and make 12 patties.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese with milk.
Pour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 12 x 9-inch pan.

title: kentucky biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk.
Mix quickly to make a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead a few times to make a soft dough. Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. With knife, cut dough into 12 even portions.
Do not separate. Bake at 400° until golden.
Brush with butter.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg in a medium bowl; set aside.
Combine flour, garlic salt, paprika, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
Dip chicken in milk and egg.
Batter in flour mixture.
Fry in deep fat.

title: butterflake hors d'oeuvres
directions: Separate rolls and pat into greased mini muffin tins.
Drain tuna thoroughly and place in bowl.
Break up.
Spoon into rolls.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut all fruit fine.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at moderate temperature until done.
(I always put a pan of water in the oven to keep it from drying out.)

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Cook to soft to hard ball - 238° to 240°. Test for firmness wanted by dropping 1/2 teaspoon in cold water.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease loaf pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating one at a time in butter and sugar mix.

Sift all-purpose flour, salt and baking soda together. Stir dry mix and whole-wheat flour into cream mix. Fold in bananas, vanilla and walnuts. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove from loaf pan and cool on rack.

title: pecan pie tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium sized bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon into pie tart shells or pour into crusts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until filling is set and crusts are golden brown.

title: au gratin potatoes casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices (leaving peels on) to equal about 8 cups.
Cook and stir onion and onion soup mix in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 3 cups cheese and a dash of Tabasco sauce. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Place potatoes in ungreased large baking dish.
Slice up kielbasa and put in dish.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and kielbasa. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Mix remaining cheese and crushed croutons and sprinkle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until top is brown and bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: kay's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth and drain.
Combine mushrooms, chicken soup, chicken and sour cream.
Add to noodles.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix lettuce and chilled beans.
Set in refrigerator to keep crisp.
When ready for salad to be served, mix and toss with other ingredients.

title: baked cinnamon chips
directions: Place round tortilla shells on baking sheet. Sprinkle or spray lightly with water to lightly wet top of tortilla shell completely. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake in oven at 350° until light golden brown or crispiness occurs. Break or cut apart into chip dipping pieces. Place in bowl along side of apple berry salsa and enjoy!!!

title: mcdonald's biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine the baking mix, buttermilk, sugar, salt and half of the melted margarine in a medium bowl. Mix until well-blended.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead for about 30 seconds, or until dough becomes elastic.

title: english toffee
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Butter it well.
Melt 6 Hershey bars on foil in pan; spread and refrigerate.
Cook butter and sugar together, stirring constantly until golden tan and crack stage (300°).
Pour over chocolate while still very hot.
Break up remaining 6 Hershey bars and spread over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle peanut butter morsels on bottom of crust.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add cocoa and stir until smooth.
Add milk and water and stir until blended.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Remove from
heat.
Pour into crust.
Bake 30 minutes or until edges are set.

title: yummy potatoes(oven roasted)
directions: Shake all ingredients in Glad bag, then empty into roasting pan in single layer.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook chicken, water, sherry, salt, onion, curry powder and celery for 1 hour. Remove chicken from stove and debone when cool. Saute mushrooms in butter.
Cook rice in broth (make up to required volume with water).
Mix chicken, rice, mushrooms, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Put in 3-quart baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Beat sugar and cocoa into this.
Add vanilla and pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Chill to set.

title: key lime pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs well. Add condensed milk. Mix in lime juice and rind, a little at a time. Beat until stiff. Stir in sugar, salt and food coloring. Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool, chill and serve.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Take turkey and wash thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Other seasonings may be used such as sage, Cajun seasoning, etc.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add sauces, soup and tomatoes. In a baking dish, layer half of meat mixture, 1 package chips and half of cheese slices. Repeat layers and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and mix.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham delites
directions: Split tea rolls (slice in half and put bottom half back in foil pan).
Spread mixture of mustard, onion, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and butter or margarine on bottom half of tea rolls.
Layer with ham and cheese.
Cover with top of tea rolls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: captain's casserole
directions: Combine rice, oregano and pepper in a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow dish.
Heat soup, milk and cheese until cheese is melted. Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Stir 1 1/2 cups tomato juice into rice (add water to make 1 1/2 cups, if needed).
Arrange most of sliced tomatoes on rice.
Add onion, tuna and olives.
Pour on cheese sauce.
Add remaining tomatoes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put blueberries in pie shell. Spread mixture over berries.
Mix 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes for fresh berries.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes for frozen berries.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture into pan..
Chill until set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Pour on remaining Jell-O and chill until firm.
Cut into squares or scoop out with spoon.

title: orange cranberry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine the pie crust mix, brown sugar, baking soda, and cinnamon in the bowl of a food processor (or electric mixer). Pulse two or three times just to mix.
Add eggs and process until well mixed. Stir in cranberries, pecans and butterscotch morsels.
Drop from heaping teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing the cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet to rack for cooling.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk and shortening.
Put sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and cool.
Add a little flour and beaten eggs.
Stir and add the 1/4 cup warm water and yeast.
Add enough flour to knead.
Knead and let rise until double.
Roll out rolls and let rise.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: Combine orange and cranberry juices in a large pitcher or small punch bowl with ice.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: dressing
directions: Cook giblets and some extra chicken.
Cut up meat and add broth, sauteed onion, salt and beaten eggs to bread.
Mix.

title: salsiccia con vino rosso(sausage with burgundy)
directions: Cut sausage in 4-inch long pieces.
Place in pan and cover with water.
Cover with lid and boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Prick sausage with fork to allow fat to escape. Cook with lid off for 15 to 20 minutes, until all water has evaporated and sausage is brown.
Gradually add Burgundy, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Serves 5 to 7.

title: breakfast eggs(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hash browned creamed potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 2 hours.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper well.
Add soup mixture to hash browns.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a large covered pan, cook zucchini, carrots and onion with butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 7 cups.

title: filling for cake
directions: Beat peaches, syrup and all in a bowl with electric mixer until peaches are mashed.
Put in pot with cornstarch.
Beat well and cook until thickened, about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Let cool and put between cake layers.
Excellent with "2 Egg Cake" recipe.

title: raspberry tea mix
directions: Combine until mixture is blended. Store in jar or container.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Clean and boil chicken until tender and chop.
Cook spaghetti and drain. Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and pour into casserole dish.
Place cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and beat well with mixer.
Pour mixture into container which can be sealed.
Add 1 garlic clove (whole) and store in refrigerator.
Age the dressing for about 1 week for full flavor.
Keeps indefinitely and gets better with age.

title: creamy spaghetti dinner
directions: Brown meat with cut-up onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix together Cheddar cheese, cream of mushroom soups and tomato sauce.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir and simmer for a few minutes, then add corn and water; simmer.
Pour over cooked spaghetti and serve.

title: caramel bread rolls
directions: Cut one loaf of bread dough into 8 pieces.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix thoroughly the brown sugar, pudding, butter, milk and spices.
Sprinkle bread slices with nuts, raisins and 1/2 the crushed pineapple.
Pour half of the creamy mixture over top.
Slice the remaining loaf of bread into 8 pieces and place them on top of the creamy layer.
Sprinkle this loaf with raisins, nuts and remaining pineapple.
Pour remaining creamy mixture over it.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked ham
directions: Make diagonal slits 1/4-inch deep across ham to get a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, basting often with a combination of orange juice, pineapple juice, corn syrup and brown sugar.
Spoon preserves over ham and bake 30 minutes longer. Cool slightly before slicing.

title: frozen berry cake
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar in a medium bowl.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Place strawberry mixture in blender.
Add milk.
Pour into a large bowl.
Gently stir in whipped topping until well blended.
Freeze 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature so it can be scooped out.
Garnish with more toppings and strawberries. Makes 10 servings.

title: turtle candies
directions: Microwave morsels in glass bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until smooth.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Drop chocolate by tablespoonfuls onto a waxed paper lined baking sheet, shaping into 16 (1 1/2 inch) circles.
Reserve the remaining chocolate.
Arrange 4 pecan halves over each circle. Chill until firm.

title: aunt gibby's garlic dill pickles(makes 8 to 10 quarts)
directions: Scrub cukes and refrigerate overnight.
Pack into sterilized quart jars.
Add 1 each of garlic, onion slice, red pepper and dill sprig.

title: lemon tassies
directions: Mix 1/4 c. butter and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add flour and beat until crumbly.
Shape dough into ball.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening and butter.
In this, add the beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to mixture using 2 1/2 cups more flour, then stir in walnuts.
Form into long rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake on greased sheet at 400° until brown (8 to 12 minutes).

title: snowballs(cookies)
directions: Melt butter;
add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl mix flour, salt and nuts.
Put both ingredients together, then add chocolate	chips.	Make
dough
into
balls.
Put on ungreased cookie
sheet.
Bake
at
350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Layer bread in well-greased large pan.
Spread Cheddar cheese over bread.
Place sausage or ham on top of cheese.
Beat eggs; combine with milk, dry mustard and mushroom soup.
Mix well and pour over the bread, cheese and meat.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble ground beef in heated frypan.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Finely chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Add to ground beef and cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour or until thickened.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs thoroughly in bowl.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt until blended.
Shape dough by teaspoons into balls.

title: free soup
directions: Boil all ingredients one hour.
Have a bowl anytime!

title: baked chicken pie
directions: In butter saute onions until soft, but not brown.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in broth; cook until sauce starts to thicken.
Place chicken and vegetables in 2 quart casserole. Pour broth mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Top with ready mix biscuits or use a butter crust.
Bake 375° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Serves 6.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Put chicken, soup and broth in bottom.
Layer chicken, vegetables and eggs.
Mix flour, milk and oleo in jar.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° approximately 30 minutes (until crust is brown).

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix all together and mash with fork into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool.

title: historic natchitoches hot-ta-meat pie
directions: Make a roux of shortening and flour; add other ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook thoroughly and let cool completely before placing it on dough.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cover raisins with water; add cloves and allow to simmer until the raisins are tender.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture, stirring until slightly thickened.
Add butter and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve hot over ham slices.

title: rice and chili
directions: Mix rice and cheese soup well.
Put in 9-inch pie plate, raising sides like pie crust.
Put chili in center.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes; cut.
Garnish with sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: cracker jack
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, butter, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour over popped corn and mix.
Spread on two buttered cookie sheets and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Break apart while still warm.

title: tarragon squash
directions: Steam squash with tarragon.
Add sugar, salt and margarine; toss.

title: spinach with eggs
directions: In large iron skillet sprayed with nonstick butter flavored cooking spray at high heat, stir-fry the spinach until done.
Stir constantly and do not add water.
When done, toss scrambled eggs on top and serve.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Combine canned chicken and canned soup.
Heat with low flame, stirring frequently. Cook egg noodles and drain.
When soup boils, pour over egg noodles and mix (do not overcook noodles or you will have a gooey mess).
Serve with canned biscuits.
Makes about 8 to 10 good size servings.

title: ice cream cone cakes(cupcakes)
directions: Make cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter into each cone about 2/3 full in each cone.
Bake in cupcake pans according to cake directions.
Cool.
Swirl icing on cake to give ice cream appearance.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make salad dressing by combining mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Dressing can be used immediately, but is best if allowed to sit for three to four hours.

title: play dough(noncook)
directions: Add food coloring to water.
Stir all ingredients together with spoon.
Knead to workable consistency.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture alternately with apple and sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: liver baked with onions
directions: Spray 2 quart casserole dish with PAM.
Place half, or cover bottom of dish with onions.
Season liver with salt and pepper and dredge with flour.
Place liver over onions and sprinkle with parsley (if making several layers, you can repeat with sliced onions, liver, parsley, mushrooms, etc.).
Cover liver with sliced mushrooms and remaining onion slices.
Season with a little more salt and pepper.
Pour melted butter over top or dot with butter. Pour bouillon and red wine over top.
Add bay leaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes or until done (if baking several layers, you may want to bake a little longer).

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Steam the mushrooms for 1 minute.
In a saucepan combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for a few minutes.
Place mushrooms in a glass or ceramic bowl and add the marinade.
Let marinate in the refrigerator at least 24 hours. Serve with a toothpick.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° in glass dish until set and brown on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk,
condensed milk and pudding mix 10 minutes in blender (until soupy).
Mix in Cool Whip on low;
cut bananas. Layer with cookies on bottom.

title: huckleberry cheese dessert
directions: Cream the cheese and powdered sugar together; fold in Cool Whip.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Blend pickle juice and mustard with mayonnaise.
Add to potatoes and mix well.
Add spices. Cover salad and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, tuck lettuce around edge and garnish with tomatoes or radishes.
Serves 8.

title: dip for sliced fruit
directions: Add orange and lemon juices to Marshmallow Creme.
Whip until fluffy; add mayonnaise and whip again until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: black-eyed pea soup with ham
directions: Saute onions, celery, green pepper, garlic, pork and ham.
Add to black-eyed peas after boiling about 5 minutes.
Simmer until black-eyed peas are done.
Serve with white rice as side dish.

title: chicken in a puff
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Unfold pastry and roll out to make 4 7x10-inch rectangles.
Do 2nd sheet of pastry the same way.
Mix cheese, garlic, salt, pepper and watercress together.

title: sarah bogdan's fiesta orange chiffon mold
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in cold water and orange juice.
Chill until thick (approximately 1 1/2 hours). Blend all of Cool Whip into jello (use mixer) or save part of Cool Whip as a topping.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook one minute, stirring.
Gradually add milk and broth, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, garlic powder and basil.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook over medium heat until broccoli is tender.
A family favorite.

title: festive black-eyed peas
directions: Cook ham hock until tender.
Wash peas and cook until nearly done and then boil on low.
Add green pepper, onion and pimiento. Cook until vegetables are done.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion together.
Add ground beef and brown. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with butter until it becomes dry and crumbly. Put this on top of applesauce in an ovenproof bowl.
Cook at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put oven on broil and brown top.

title: everybody's favorite dessert
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool!!

title: parmesan baked ocean perch
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and seasonings. Melt butter. Dip fish in butter, then flour mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until perch flakes easily with a fork. Makes 4 servings.

title: zesty chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan combine uncooked rice, 1/2 can French fried onions and Italian seasoning.
Pour bouillon over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken halves on top; pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Place veggies around chicken, covering rice only.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is done.
Top chicken with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes until onions are golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften all cheeses to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor until fluffy.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Shape into balls.
Yields 2 small balls or 1 large ball.

title: carrot fudge
directions: Cook carrots, sugar, milk and water to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Remove from fire; add flavoring and cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan; pat down to 1-inch depth and when firm, cut into squares.
The grain is likely to be a little coarse due to the grated carrots.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Spread in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mjeddra
directions: Half and thinly slice onions.
Fry in oil until dark brown. Remove 1/4, draining on paper towel; reserve.
Add lentils, stirring briefly.
Add bouillon, pepper and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil and cook, covered, over low heat until lentils are almost tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Add salted water to cover lentils by about 1/8-inch.
Liquid should taste strongly of salt and lemon juice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain excess water.
Add salad dressing.
Slice cucumber thinly and add to salad.
Mince onion and add to salad. Add Durkee Salad Sensations.
Mix into salad.
Top salad with a little extra Salad Sensations for a garnish.

title: chicken parisian
directions: Oil a 10-inch saute pan.
Flour chicken and lightly saute.
Add mushrooms, white wine, thyme, paprika and chicken stock.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Put a pat of butter in flour and drop in saute pan until creamy.
Serve over rice.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies(soft)
directions: Cream butter well.
Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet, well apart.
With spatula, flatten into circles about 2-inches in diameter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 30 (3-inch) cookies.

title: tuna casserole with cheese swirls
directions: Cook onion in shortening until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup Bisquick.
Add soup; gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in tuna, peas and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into ungreased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Keep hot in oven while preparing biscuits.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling; add walnuts and heat to boiling, cook 1 minute.
Rinse walnuts under running hot water; drain.
Wash the saucepan and dry well.
In large bowl with rubber spatula, gently stir warm walnuts with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
(If necessary, let mixture stand a few minutes to dissolve sugar.)

Meanwhile, in same pan over medium heat, heat about 1 inch salad oil to 350° on deep fat thermometer. With slotted spoon, add the nuts (a few spoonfuls at a time) to the oil; fry until golden, stirring often.
With slotted spoon, place walnuts in sieve over bowl to drain; sprinkle lightly with salt. Toss lightly to keep walnuts from sticking together.
Transfer to cookie sheet to cool, separating them.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: sauce for fish(saus for fisk)
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients well.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in half.
Put 1/2 crumbled cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Put 1/2 pudding over cake next, 1/2 pie filling next, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and cool in refrigerator at least 6 hours.

title: crispy critters
directions: Cook together sugar and Karo until dissolved.
Mix in peanut butter; remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; mix completely. Pour into buttered cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch or peanut butter chips together in double boiler.
Spread on crispy mixture.
Cut into squares before refrigerating.
Let set until the chocolate is set, 1 hour. Serve.

title: beef steak parmesan
directions: Pound steak; trim off fat and cut in pieces.
Dip in egg; roll in Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Lay in shallow baking dish in one layer.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco,
brown
sugar,
white
sugar and vanilla.
Add in well beaten eggs and pineapple.
Stir together salt, baking powder,
baking
soda
and flour,
then add to creamed mixture.
Drop on
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
(You may add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.)
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: vidalia onion and potato casserole
directions: Season meat and brown in skillet.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions thinly.
Alternate layers of potatoes, onions and meat. Pour mushroom soup (undiluted) over all and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until done.
Cool, then peel to cube potatoes.
Mix Miracle Whip, prepared mustard, sugar and salt together.
Add the other ingredients and stir.
Then keep refrigerated.
Slice 4 hard-boiled eggs on top or stir in as you choose before serving.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper mixing well.
Carefully blend in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
(Do not boil.)
Stir into beans and put into casserole.
Top with cheese and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.
Use 1-quart size casserole.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
Starting with 1/4 cup milk, add gradually. More can be added if needed to make a firm dough.
Pinch off and roll out real thin.
Cut; drop in boiling broth.
These can be frozen after being rolled out and cut.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix and press flour, nuts and oleo in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Bake in 425° oven 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 Cool Whip (6 ounces).
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings, milk and vanilla.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Shave Hershey bar on top.
Refrigerate.

title: children's treat from canada
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl or large grocery bag.
Sprinkle with jello and toss to mix.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: baked northern pike
directions: Parboil fish in chicken bouillon.
Place, belly down, in oblong baking dish, spreading with butter.
Bake in moderate oven until it begins to brown.
Sprinkle with juice of a whole lemon.

title: one dish chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix stuffing mix, water and butter and set aside.
Place chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add vegetables.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Makes 6 servings.

title: crisp lemon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, working quickly so that the butter does not harden.
Roll into 1-inch balls and then flatten.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 minute, then remove from sheet.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: hamburger-corn bake
directions: Combine meat, onion, catsup, salt, chili powder and oregano in 10-inch skillet.
Brown and drain.
Grease 10-inch pie plate; line with meat.
Pour corn into center of meat shell.
Prepare muffin mix as directed, adding butter.
Spread evenly over meat and corn.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.
Combine remaining sauce ingredients; heat and serve with meat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all thoroughly together.
Place in a greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: two cup cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, pineapple and coconut together.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Do not cover.
In morning, add Cool Whip.
Bake the lemon cake as directed on box.
When cool, split the layers and add the topping.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: In a bowl, mix baking soda and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add water.
Stir until thickens.
Add sugar, eggs, rest of butter, then rest of ingredients.
Can add chocolate chips at this point.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy shrimp scampi
directions: Cook onion and garlic, in butter in large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tarragon, lemon juice, steak sauce, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly, 5 to 6 minutes (until shrimp turns pink).
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over pasta.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix together everything except meat and spices. Boil 20 minutes. Pour liquid over meat and spices. Mix well. Heat up. Simmer a short time. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in single layer in large skillet. Sprinkle with chilies, tomatoes, onion, salt and cumin.
Add broth.
Heat over medium heat until chicken is very tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken pieces from skillet, shaking off pieces of vegetables.
Let cool.

title: tex-mex deviled eggs
directions: Cut the tips off both ends of each egg to create a flat surface for the eggs to stand on.
Slice each egg in half crosswise. Remove yolks.
Place in small bowl and mash.
Add green onions, cilantro, Serrano or jalapeno pepper, mayonnaise and mustard. Blend well.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon yolk mixture into each egg half.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: penne with broccoli
directions: Rinse broccoli; cut into flowerets.
Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Peel and chop onion.
Clean and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter in a large skillet.
Saute onion and mushrooms with basil, oregano and salt until soft.
Add broccoli. Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to combine.
Add milk.
Heat to a boil, stirring.
Lower the heat.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese and half of Parmesan.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear
lettuce, rinse.
Wrap in dish towel and refrigerate. Mash
garlic
in wooden salad bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients, stirring constantly.
Toss lettuce in dressing, top with cheese. Serve immediately.

title: pecan yummys
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and coat well.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let pecans set for 30 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.
These are very good.

title: chicken in a pocket
directions: Spray a piece of foil with Pam.
Layer ingredients in order given, spreading mayo and mustard over chicken breast.
Close foil tightly.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco seasoning together in a small bowl. Spread bean dip on the bottom of a 10-inch fairly deep dish or pizza pan. Spread the thawed avocado dip on top of the bean dip and spread the sour cream mixture on top of the avocado. Sprinkle chopped onions on top of the sour cream, then diced tomatoes. Cover with chopped olives and grated cheese. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Fold in chocolate chips. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix together as pastry.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake(student favorite)
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together the graham crackers and the melted 1/2 cup butter.
Press crumb mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the remaining 1/2 cup butter about 30 seconds until softened.
Add powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Spread mixture over crumbs mixture.
Slice bananas lengthwise into halves and arrange over egg mixture.
Spoon pineapple or strawberries over bananas.
Spread with dessert topping.
Sprinkle with chocolate and the nuts, if desired.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Cut into about 12 squares to serve.
Top each square with a cherry.
Serves 12.
Time:
About 5 hours before serving.

title: calabasita(mexican zucchini stew)
directions: Cut meat from roast into bite size pieces.
Brown well in large stock pot in oil.
Cut zucchini in bite size chunks.
Add to browned meat along with the onion, green pepper, tomatoes, spices and salt.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes on medium-low heat.
Stir about every 10 minutes to prevent sticking.
Then add corn and simmer 5 minutes more.
Just before serving, mix the cornstarch in 1/2 cup cold water and add to the stew to thicken.
Stir well.
Turn off heat and cover until ready to serve.
Serves 6 or more.
Flour tortillas are a nice accompaniment with this.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine until reaches rolling boil. Cook 1 1/2 minutes more. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: cheesy mexican casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground chuck.
Add all except Cheddar cheese, chip and peppers.
Heat until cream cheese melts.
Cover bottom of casserole with crushed chips.
Pour in meat mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with chips and peppers.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Beat
with	electric
mixer for four minutes on minimum speed. Prepare 2 (9-inch) cake pans by greasing with shortening and flouring.
Pour
batter into pans.	Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: louisiana hush puppies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add enough milk to make mixture the consistency of whipped cream.
Drop full teaspoons into hot grease.
Serves 6-8.

title: steak and mushrooms
directions: Put steak into roasting pan with the cooked steak broth.
Put in the potatoes and onions; bake until potatoes are done.
Drain any juice from the steak and potatoes.
Add the soup, spreading over steak and potatoes.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: gooies
directions: Mix butter, 1 egg, nuts and cake mix, then pat out in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex.
Stir cream cheese, then add sugar and 2 eggs alternately, beginning and ending with sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: ellie's fettuccine
directions: Cook Fettuccine as directed.
Drain well and place in warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add butter, cream, grated cheese and parsley.
Toss until Fettuccine is well coated.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.

title: "chocolate no-bake oatmeal cookies"
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a saucepan. Add butter and milk. Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and chill. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and allspice.
Pour into sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in the chopped apples, raisins, black walnuts, and vanilla.
Turn into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Take chicken off bone.
Butter pan.
Put chicken in pan.
Whip sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Put on top of chicken and cream sauce.
Sprinkle chicken broth over entire pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add onion flakes, tomato paste and two tomato paste cans of water, mixing well. Add seasonings and spices.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese in two 9 x 13-inch pans. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add potatoes, onion, salt and paprika.
Cook until vegetables are lightly brown and tender.
Add milk and cheese; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is hot and cheese is melted and smooth.
Spoon into 4 soup bowls and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In skillet, mix chicken with all ingredients (except cheese, tortillas, olives and sour cream).
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Layer in casserole dish using tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Top and seal with sour cream.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: all star vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan with oil; sprinkle with cornmeal. Unroll dough; press in greased pan.
Spread pizza sauce over dough within 1-inch of edges.
Arrange mushrooms, zucchini, red onion and green and red pepper rings over sauce.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.

Melt butter, stir in stuffing. In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer stuffing, one-half chicken, cream of chicken diluted with 3/4 can of broth, stuffing, 1/2 chicken and cream of mushroom soup diluted with 3/4 can of broth.
Sprinkle with stuffing.
Bake covered 45 minutes at 400°.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put into a large rectangular pan or into muffin tins that have paper muffin cups.
Freeze!
Use as salad or dessert.
Keeps well for weeks.
When frozen in paper cups in muffin tins, they may be removed from the tins and place in a freezer bag.
Take out as needed.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease generously a 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer rice or noodles first, then dot with margarine. Layer chicken, then cans of soup.
Put water on top.
Put lid on casserole.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Do not open casserole to see if done!
Remove from oven; allow to cool only 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove lid.
Eat and enjoy!

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil the butter, cocoa and water. Pour over the flour and sugar. Add the buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix margarine,	flour and powdered sugar.
Pat into pie plate. Bake
at 325° for 25 minutes.
Time of preparation: 15 minutes.

title: devil's delight
directions: Crumble cookies in the bottom of a cake pan.
Layer with pudding and Cool Whip until all are used.
Refrigerate.

title: 15 minute mexicali supper
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown, stirring to break up meat.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and corn.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.
Let
rise
minutes; work down and let rise 15 minutes more.
Put in pan;
let rise another 15 minutes, then bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: coffee bars
directions: In bowl, sift flour, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar.
Beat 2 eggs and add coffee.
Add this to dry mixture, then add vanilla and oil.
Grease a large 15 x 11 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread dough.
Sprinkle top with chocolate bits and walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Moist and yummy!

title: "birds"
directions: Salt and pepper birds.
Place in a roasting pan and lay bacon over them.
Partly cover with water.
Steam covered on top of the stove for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Spread flour in a shallow pan and place in a 300° oven for about 1 hour or until browned, stirring occasionally.
Brown butter in a skillet.
When birds are tender, turn up the fire and add more water, if necessary, to have sufficient for gravy.
Sprinkle with 3 or 4 tablespoons of the browned flour, adding the remainder to water in the pan.
Pour hot butter over birds.
Place in a 400° oven 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 portions.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season the chops with salt and pepper. Arrange in a baking pan that is large enough so they will not be crowded.
Combine the sugar, catsup and cold water.
Pour over the chops and place an onion slice over each one.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover pan, baste with sauce and continue baking until brown and very tender.

title: chocolate marshmallow dominoes
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with aluminum foil.
Arrange marshmallows in rows over foil.
Melt chocolate chips on very low heat.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Blend well.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallows.
With back of spoon, work chocolate into spaces on all sides of marshmallows.
Chill for 2 hours or until chocolate hardens.
Turn candy out of pan upside down.
Pull off foil.
Cut into 36 pieces with a marshmallow in center of each.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and salt, then blend 2 tablespoons vinegar and grated onion.
Gradually beat in oil.
Beat until thick and light.
Slowly beat in remaining vinegar.
Stir in celery seed. Pour into jars.
Shake good before using.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix with the 1 stick butter.
Use fingers to crumble together real well (fine).
Spread over pineapple, cherry mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Serve with Cool Whip or a scoop of ice cream.
Can be made the day before using.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and freeze 24 hours.
Take from freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Mash 4 bananas and add to the above mixture.
Add 7-Up.
This will be slushy when served.
One to two cups vodka (optional) can also be added.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place chicken breasts, bowed side up, between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap.
Pound from center out to form cutlets not quite 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt, sprinkle with garlic salt and snipped parsley over cutlets.
Chill.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix all together and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick stuck in middle comes out clean.

title: jiffy chicken pie
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add soup, chicken and seasonings. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with biscuits and bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and salt thoroughly.
Bring milk to scalding and gradually add the dry ingredients, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water stirring often until thick.
Add the butter and egg yolks and cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool and add the vanilla.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat water, butter, sugar and salt to boiling in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Whisk in corn meal and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened for about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and place in large bowl.
Whisk in milk until smooth.
Add eggs and baking powder.
Pour in pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk, stirring well. Add onion and blend (mixture will be thick).
Dip a large spoon into hot salad oil, then into batter for each hush puppy.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling
water until tender.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips;
set
aside.
Combine 1/4 cup margarine and next 5 ingredients
in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Pour this mixture over potatoes
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then mix
cup
margarine
melted with herb seasoned stuffing (about 1 1/2
cups) on top of cheese.
Place in 350° oven.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese. Mix with sugar and cocoa. Add vanilla and nuts. Spread in buttered pan.

title: curried chicken sandwich spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, onion, curry powder and salt.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 2 cups.

title: french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Add chili powder to egg white.
Dip potatoes in egg mixture.
Place on foil lined pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except potato chips and cheese in greased
casserole	dish.
Crush
potato
chips
over
top and cheese over that.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: ravioli primavera
directions: Bring marinara sauce and water to a boil in a large nonstick skillet.
Stir in ravioli.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring a few times with a rubber spatula, for 15 minutes.
Add mixed vegetables.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring gently 2 or 3 times or until vegetables are tender.
If desired, stir in basil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: browned beef stew
directions: Flour the beef stew meat while the oil is heating in a large skillet.
Brown a few pieces at a time removing the pieces as they are brown.
Add onion and garlic to the remainder of the oil. Simmer a few minutes. Add the water to make a gravy.
Add the salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and beef bouillon. Stir and simmer until well mixed.
Return the meat.
Add the potatoes, carrots and peas.
Simmer until the potatoes and carrots are done and meat is tender, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.

title: peanut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, salt and vanilla; continue to beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican white bean chili
directions: Mix unrinsed, undrained beans with salsa in large pot or crock-pot.
Add chicken, if desired.
Simmer at least one hour (the longer the better) or in crock-pot all day.
Add milk, a little at a time if needed, if too thick.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and serve with tortilla chips.

title: dutch chocolate bars
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions. When thick and boiling, add cake mix (dry) and mix thoroughly.
It will be very thick and almost mealy.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips, sprinkled evenly.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: To make roux:
Heat bacon drippings in skillet until hot.
Add flour and stir over medium heat until chocolate brown.
Add onions and celery.
Brown another 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to roux.
Add 1 quart of water to dissolve.
Add another quart of water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Bring to a boil; add okra, Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add shrimp and crabmeat.
Done when shrimp are tender.
Do not overcook, shrimp will be tough.
Eat over hot fluffy rice.

title: yankee doodle dandees
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts and chow mein noodles until thoroughly covered with chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets lined with waxed paper; refrigerate until hard.

title: million dollar rice
directions: Cook rice for 25 minutes or until water is gone.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter and set aside after transferring to baking dish.
Use remaining butter to saute mushrooms for 4 minutes. Stir into rice and season with salt and pepper.
Cover baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 250°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. When they are well blended, pour into graham cracker crust. Freeze for several hours. Let thaw for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Shape into 12 large meatballs with 1 cube of Mozzarella cheese in center of each, making sure cheese is completely covered. Coat each meatball with flour and brown in pan with salad oil in it.
After browned, put in casserole dish and cover with pizza sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: jam coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and margarine into biscuit mix until crumbly. Blend in 1/3 cup milk.
Turn onto floured surface; knead 8 to 10 strokes.
On waxed paper roll into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Turn onto greased baking sheet; remove paper.
Spread with preserves. Make 2 1/4 inch cuts at 1 inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over filling.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: boeuf a la forester
directions: Slice meat in 1/2-inch strips and dredge in flour.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet and brown meat.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook a few minutes longer.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart casserole and add bay leaf, allspice and wine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Chop or blend the cranberries, one cup at a time.
Add the sugar; let set for 15 minutes.
Add the celery, apples and pecans or walnuts; set aside.
Sprinkle the gelatin over the orange juice in a small saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute, then heat over low heat, stirring, until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir into cranberry mixture, then place all into a lightly oiled 1-quart mold. Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours, until set.
Garnish and serve with mayonnaise, or eat as is.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.

title: jello dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and oleo. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: quick mexican spread
directions: Combine cheese and chilies, mixing until well blended.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips or spread over warm tortillas or cornbread.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with sugar.
In a large bowl, add pineapple, strawberries, nuts, bananas and Cool Whip.
Gently mix, then add the cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into large container and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 15 minutes. Beat softened cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in small mixing bowl while crust is chilling. Fold in half of Cool Whip. Spread mixture over chilled crust. Prepare pudding according to directions on box except use 3 1/2 cups milk. Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill 2 hours. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.

title: broccoli platter
directions: Cook the butter and onion together in a small skillet over medium heat until the onion is soft.
Do not let it brown.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the sour cream, poppy seed, paprika, salt and pepper.
Heat in the top of a double boiler over boiling water. Cook the broccoli.
Lift onto a warm platter and pour on the hot sauce.
Sprinkle on chopped peanuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy pretzel dippers
directions: Cut Cheddar cheese into 16 cubes. Insert a thin pretzel stick into each cube. Serve as dippers with honey Dijon mustard.

title: best banana bread
directions: Mix together (no particular order).
Mixture will be very thick.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about an hour, more or less.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and jam.
Combine flour and spices, leaving out a small amount of flour to coat raisins and nuts.
Mix batter, dry ingredients, buttermilk and soda.
Add raisins and nuts that have been coated in flour.
Pour in 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool and ice.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows, Hershey bars and milk over low heat.
Cool and add 1 carton Cool Whip.
Chill 4 hours and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in other ingredients. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated and used as needed.

title: berry bars
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar, baking powder and oats in bowl. Cream butter into mixture; batter will be crumbly.
Spray baking dish with Pam and press mixture on bottom of dish.
Use only half of the mixture.
Spread pie filling on top of that.
Then spread remaining flour mixture over pie filling.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then cut into bars.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Blend well. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Spray Pam or oil into muffin tins.
Spread biscuits in muffin tins.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and sauce; mix well. Put meat mixture in biscuit cups.
Then put cheese on top.
Bake until biscuit is brown and cheese melted at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Add 2 cups flour, spice, soda and applesauce.
Mix well.
Sift remaining 2 cups flour over raisins, nuts and gumdrops.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and oleo.
Set 15 minutes.
Beat together eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and oleo.
Pour over crust.
Add 5 to 6 sliced bananas.
Over that, pour drained pineapple.
Top with whipped cream.
Put cherries and nuts on top.
(If don't have cream cheese, may use 2 sticks butter.)

title: sweet pickle spears
directions: Slice ends from cucumbers and cut into spears. Cover cucumbers with boiling water, let stand 2 hours. Drain and pack into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil. Pour hot liquid over cucumbers leaving 1/4 inch head space. Remove air bubbles. Adjust caps. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath. Yield about 10 half pints.

title: individual omelets
directions: Multiply by number of people you want to serve.
Beat eggs with water and salt.
Have pan hot and buttered.
Pour in eggs; when barely set sprinkle on cheese and other ingredients.
Fold over and serve.

title: bride's pie crust(never fails)
directions: Cut lard in half.
Using one half in a large bowl, cut it up in small pieces.
Store the remaining half in refrigerator.
Pour boiling water over the lard and stir until mixture is a creamy mass.
Add salt and sugar.
Stir.
Sift flour with baking powder and stir into the mixture.
Mix well with 2 knives in a crosscutting motion until completely blended.
Roll mass into 1 large ball.
Wrap in wax paper and put in the refrigerator to cool. Cut ball in half.
Make 9-inch pie crust (2-crust pie). Refrigerate other half.
This will keep 1 week or more.

title: swiss cheese bread appetizer
directions: Slice bread loaf partly through diagonally in both directions making little diamonds.
Stuff slices of cheese in openings.
Place loaf on foil on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour mixture over bread.
Seal foil tightly around loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Check several times to be sure bottom is not browning too quickly.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to package. Do not rinse.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar, milk, flour and vanilla.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes until sugar is dissolved.

title: peach mold
directions: Drain peaches, saving 1 cup juice for jello.
Heat juice; add to jello and cool.
Cream together cream cheese and peaches with mixer.
Add Cool Whip to jello and fold together or beat slowly with mixer.
Chill.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
(If not using immediately, cool somewhat, transfer to a container with cover and refrigerate.)
Use as a barbecue sauce for chicken or ribs.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with Miracle Whip. Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Serve with Parma Dip if you wish.

title: portuguese kale soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large pot with salt.
Add beef shanks and sausage (cut sausage into 1 1/2 to 2-inch chunks).
Lower heat and simmer about 2 hours.

title: butterscotch coconut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in microwave 1 minute. Stir in brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes 32 brownies.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars; beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Place cream cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap; shape into a ball. (I wrap this in plastic wrap.) Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Roll cheese ball in pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter elf bites
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Stir in cereal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Combine spaghetti, butter or margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Press into a buttered casserole dish.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Combine spaghetti sauce and ground beef.
Spread over cottage cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes more. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Stir Cool Whip and Jell-O in large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, oranges and pineapple, stirring well.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix milk and flour.
Cook on low heat, stirring frequently until consistency of oatmeal.
Cool well in refrigerator.
Cream 1 cup butter and 1 cup sugar until light, lemon-yellow color.
Add vanilla and cooled milk mixture.
Mixture has to be cooled or you will ruin frosting.
Makes enough to frost a 4 layer cake.

title: shrimp toast pupu
directions: Mix altogether except bread.
Cut bread into fourths, square or triangles.
Trim off crust.
Spread mixture on bread and deep fry shrimp side down first, then turn over and cook until brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare
German
chocolate cake mix as directed; adding 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 1/2 stick butter.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased pan and bake at 350° until done.
While baking; combine the remaining ingredients except the leftover batter, chocolate chips and pecans; melt slowly over low heat. Pour
over cake
and
sprinkle the chocolate chips and pecans over this. Pour remaining batter and bake again 15 minutes.

title: sylvia's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and stir into first mixture.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Add pumpkin and butter.
Top with meringue made of three egg whites and nine teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until top is brown.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pack apples in jars.
Combine remaining ingredients except water and lemon juice; stir in water and cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice; pour over apples and seal.
Cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar. Beat until very stiff; add vanilla.
(Now no more electric mixer.) You add crackers and mix by hand.
Add nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until light beige.
Cool.

title: sauerkraut cold slaw
directions: Mix all the vegetables together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pimento can be added for color. Refrigerate.
The longer it stands the better.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Combine cream cheese and whipped topping in a mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Sprinkle with gelatin; mix well.
Fold in strawberries and pineapple gently.
Spoon into parfait glasses. Chill until serving time.
Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: grace george's white cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder, 2 or 3 times.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix flour and milk alternately.
Bake in layers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix green chilies, Milnot and soups together for sauce.
Brown flour tortillas, put chicken mixed with the sauce into the tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, orange and sugar.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Gently stir in cranberry mixture, pineapple, pecans and celery.
Spoon mixture into 5-cup mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce lined serving plate. Yields 8 servings.

title: philly steak sandwich
directions: In a large frying pan, combine roast beef, onion and Worcestershire. Cook until roast beef begins to wrinkle and onions are tender. Mix together mayonnaise and horseradish in separate bowl. Put meat, cheese and mayonnaise mixture on a hoagie roll and microwave for about 15 seconds.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Boil ribs in a pot of water with the ginger for 1 hour. Combine rest of ingredients to make the sauce.
After boiling the ribs, marinate for 1 hour in the sauce.
Barbecue over charcoal or oven broil until brown.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to package directions in the form of a sheet cake. Cool completely and then cut in small cubes. Mix both boxes of pudding according to directions on package. In a large bowl layer: 1/2 of the cake, 1/2 the pudding, 1/2 the Cool Whip, 1/2 the Skor bars. Repeat layers, ending with crumbled candy. Chill for at least 4 hours. Makes 12 or more servings.

title: hot crab appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a shallow dish or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (8-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350°
for 35 minutes or until done.

title: mexican omelet
directions: In an 8-inch, nonstick saute pan, cook vegetables in butter until soft.
Add eggs and cook over medium heat until omelet style, stirring gently until eggs begin to set.
Flip omelet and continue cooking, but no longer than two minutes.
Add cheese and salsa. Fold in half and remove from pan.

title: witchie poo's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs in large bowl. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop dough by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheet. Cool on wire rack. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Add yeast to hot water, milk and sugar.
Let rise.
Add the rest
of
ingredients.
Knead well; let rise.
Knead down and let rise again.
I make rolls with cinnamon, sugar, butter and nuts or poppy seed.
Let rise again and bake at 350° until done.

title: mrs. nixon's hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a large rectangular baking dish.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Top with cheese mixture and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 45 minutes.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in 2 cups of water until tender.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil; simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot with saltines.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Flour and grease tube pan. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
For cupcake size, bake 15 to 20 minutes; loaf size, bake 1 hour.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable casserole dish or bowl.
Cover with top or plastic wrap.
Cook for 5 minutes on High, then 12 minutes on Medium (50% power).
Remove and let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Flake with a fork before serving.

title: ellen bryan's swedish tea ring
directions: In large bowl, put 1/2 cup warm (not hot) water, yeast and sugar.
Stir until dissolved well.
In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Pour in cold milk.
Add salt.
When melted mixture is lukewarm, pour into yeast mixture.
Add eggs and about 3 1/2 cups unsifted flour.
Stir until lumps dissolve.
Add about 3 1/2 cups of flour; stir well.
Knead well.
Let rise in bowl for about 1 hour; stir down.* Roll on a large floured space into the largest rectangle possible.
Spread completely with softened butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with box of light brown sugar and sprinkle heavily with cinnamon.
Across one long end, place the broken nuts. Start with nut side and roll like a jelly roll.
Seal edges very well.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind squash.
Grind onions.
Cover with salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain; add vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, turmeric and pepper.
Cut up red and green peppers.
Cook 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 7 pints.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together with 3 tablespoons wine vinegar and 6 tablespoons Crisco oil.
Let marinate overnight.
Serve with chips.

title: black forest cherry pie
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, coconut and flavoring.
In a separate bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar to whipped cream and fold into whipped cream cheese.
Make sure cream cheese is well blended or it will be lumpy.
Fold into cherry mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill until firm. Freezes well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked berry pudding
directions: Mix together the margarine, milk, baking powder, sugar and flour to make a dough, then spread it in a greased, deep baking dish.
Pour the berries and boiling water over the dough and bake it at 400° until the cake is done.

title: aztec tomato sauté
directions: Saute green pepper and onions until tender.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Mix well.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sugar, parsley flakes and chili seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and vanilla thoroughly in mixer.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and soda in separate bowl.
Add egg and oil mixture and stir with spoon until well mixed.
Add buttermilk, then add apples and nuts.
Stir until all ingredients are evenly mixed. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in large flat pan or 1 hour and 20 minutes in tube pan.

title: no-fat dip
directions: Drain beans.
Place all ingredients in food processor. Process until smooth.
Serve pretzels or fat-free chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in casserole dish.
Cook 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix melted Velveeta cheese, Hellmann's mayonnaise and pimento.
Pour mixture over potatoes and cook 1 additional hour.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half lengthwise; separate thighs from legs.
The chicken pieces should be all about the same size, for even cooking.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken pieces in flour and shake off excess.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs, pressing crumbs into chicken.
Gently shake off excess.
Melt lard in a chicken fryer or heavy, deep kettle. Heat to 250°.
Fry chicken pieces a few at a time for 20 minutes.
Keep fried chicken warm while frying remaining batches.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and margarine in a double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until margarine melts.
When margarine has melted, continue to cook over boiling water for 10 minutes (time is important), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes, then add marshmallows.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, margarine and water together lightly.
Put half of mixture in a buttered 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Mix chicken, onion, green onion tops, celery, mayonnaise and salt thoroughly. Spread in casserole over bread mixture.
Top with remaining bread mixture.

title: gnocchi surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients (except zucchini) well with a fork.
Wash zucchini, slice them while wet and flour them.
Put 1 or 2 zucchini slices in egg mixture at a time.
Cover them completely with egg mixture.

title: nutty raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Nuts will rise to form top crust.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in 4x sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 11 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add pumpkin, then dry ingredients, then water, stirring just until mixed.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Chop green onions fine, including some of the green ends.
Shred or grate the beef; save some to roll the ball in.
Put rest with ingredients.
Shape into ball; roll in remaining beef and refrigerate.
This is nice for Christmas.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and place in a tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: alphabet soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan; drain on paper towel.
Add onion, carrots, celery and garlic to bacon drippings in pan.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 7 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add chicken broth, basil, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni and parsley.
Cover; cook 10 minutes. Crumble bacon over soup and serve.

title: blackberry jello salad
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with sliced bananas.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bananas.
Let set until jelled.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients in pot; cook slow for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until carrots and potatoes are done.
One cup contains 55 calories, 1 g fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: eggnog
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, salt, vanilla and milk.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to very soft peaks and gently fold into milk mixture.
Stir in bourbon or brandy (chill).
Garnish with nutmeg.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tossed greens with strawberries
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl; stir well.

title: summer pasta
directions: At least an hour ahead, combine the first five ingredients and refrigerate.
Can be done the day ahead to allow the flavors to blend.
To serve:
Cook pasta according to directions until al dente. Drain.
Toss with cold tomato mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Serve immediately.

title: sweet-sour sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil together until sugar dissolves. Combine sauerkraut and vegetables in large container.
Pour dressing over vegetables, cover and refrigerate.
Serve well chilled.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 stick margarine in baking casserole dish.
Mix in soup, water and rice.
Mix well.
Saute onion and bell pepper in remaining margarine.
Mix all remaining ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until rice is tender. Broil until slightly brown on top.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt
butter
and
mix
with
cracker crumbs.
Spread on bottom
of
9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle over coconut then chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
