Spoon over Eagle Brand milk and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: candied sweet pickles
directions: DAY 1:
Wash cucumbers and place in gallon jar or crock. Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
DAY 2: Drain; cover with boiling water.
Repeat for days 3 and 4.
DAY 5:
Cut cucumbers into 1/4 inch slices.
Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and spices (which have been put into a cheesecloth bag) together for 5 minutes.
Pour over slices and let stand 24 hours.
DAY 6:
Drain syrup into sauce pan and bring to boil.
Pour over slices.
DAY 7: Repeat day 6.
DAY 8:
Drain and heat syrup and spice bag to a boil.
Add cucumber slices and bring to a boil again.
Pack in clean sterile jars and seal with new lids.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients, mix well.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks.
Add milk gradually to yolks.
Add to first mixture. Pour into pie pan lined with pastry.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Add meringue made of the two egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar, beaten until stiff.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Brown meringue lightly.

title: lemon chicken nuggets
directions: Cube chicken into bite size pieces. Marinate 30 mins. in lemon juice.
Coat with above breading and fry until golden brown.

title: strawberry icing
directions: Combine sugar and egg white and beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Fold in berries.
Delicious on angel food cake or pound cake.

title: venison chili
directions: Place oil in frying pan over medium heat and spread so it covers the surface.
Add ground meat and onion until meat is brown. Stir often to keep meat from sticking.
Add rest of the ingredients to pan.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: candy
directions: Melt chips and add nuts and noodles.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water, margarine, onion and squash.
Boil until water has all boiled out.
Put into baking dish.
Add milk and cheese.
Put cracker crumbs on top and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into small balls. Bake at 400° approximately 12 minutes or until browned. These freeze well and may be taken straight from freezer and baked.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 16.

title: lo-cal pepper steak
directions: Sliver meat in 2 x 1/4-inch pieces; soak in soy sauce (even overnight).
In skillet, saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Let simmer 1 hour.
Make paste with cornstarch and water; add to skillet.
Let simmer 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: mama's eggless chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth. Bake in greased Pyrex baking pan. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven. Frost with desired icing.

title: etowah winter salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients in a jar.
Shake well.
Toss with salad ingredients just before serving.

title: summer salad
directions: Sprinkle dry gelatin over cottage cheese and mix.
Add crushed pineapple and fold in topping.
Chill until stiff.
Serves 8 to 9 people.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook
sugar,
milk, margarine and cocoa.
When	mixture reaches
a rolling boil, add peanut butter.
Remove from heat. Add pecans and vanilla, then stir in oats.
When well blended, drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: creamy chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chocolate squares in bowl.
Let stand until cool.
Cream butter and vanilla.
Add brown sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level and pour onto a square of waxed paper.
Add soda and salt to flour and stir to blend.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and waxed paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch aluminum loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake pulls away from pan. Cool; frost if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon in a shallow bowl.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: crunchy seafood casserole
directions: Empty cream of chicken or mushroom soup and milk into a 2-quart casserole. Add tuna or crab meat, nuts, celery and onion. Mix well and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add about 3/4 of the can of chow mein noodles to the mixture and mix again. Dot with butter and cover with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This tastes great with warm biscuits!

title: three layer fudge
directions: Part 1:
Combine first 4 ingredients in a pan.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 6 minutes. Stir in bag of chocolate bits, marshmallows and vanilla. Beat until stiff by hand or mixer. Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until lightly browned in a large skillet.
Add onion after chicken is done.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Add cheese. Add spaghetti to mixture.
Meal is ready with salad and bread.

title: pickling solution
directions: Mix all together and
bring
to
a boil.
Add cucumbers or beets and bring to boil again.
Fill hot jars and seal.
I use this for beets.
You may
add
a little extra sugar if you like a sweeter solution.
If
using
cucumbers, be sure to use only the tiny ones.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix soup, sour cream and mayonnaise and stir in the spinach.
Green onions may be added and 1 can water chestnuts.
Serve as a dip for chunks of Hawaiian bread.

title: chewy pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Press in bottom of pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, beat remaining eggs, syrup, sugar and butter until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour nut mixture over cake mix mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until set. Cool completely; cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk to which soda has been added.
Mix well.
Add sifted flour and mix well again. Fold in mashed bananas and chopped pecans.
Turn batter into 2 loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Line chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Baste with butter mixture occasionally.
Pan should be covered.

title: marbled peanut butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan.
Beat cake mix (dry).
Add peanut butter, water and eggs in a large bowl on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Continue as directed in Step 4. Bake 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Cool completely.
Mix frosting and 1/2 cup of peanut butter.
Spread over top of cake. Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: shrimp and ham jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in margarine until transparent.
Add shrimp and ham and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with juice, broth, rice and seasonings.
Lower heat to simmer and cover.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Serve garnished with chopped green onions.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Layer vegetables in dish.
Mix celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise and spread over the vegetables.
Crumble the Ritz crackers and mix with the melted oleo.
Spread over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sandra's taco meat
directions: Brown hamburger in a large pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 3 hours.
Makes 6 quarts.
May freeze in separate containers for future use.

title: small cheese cake(servings:  36)
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into small cupcake papers, after placing vanilla cookie wafer in the bottom.
May top with red cherry pie filling if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttered baked potato slices
directions: Pour 1/2 melted butter into shallow dish.
Place sliced potatoes in and baste well with remaining butter, salt and pepper. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Baste with remaining butter. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Continue baking until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: mocha punch
directions: Combine water and instant coffee granules, blending well. Stir in chocolate and sugar; mix well and chill.
Add ice cream and milk to chocolate mixture just before serving, blending well with a wire whisk.
Garnish with whipped cream and grated chocolate.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken caruso
directions: In medium skillet, saute bacon until lightly browned and crisp.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cook until almost tender; stir in chicken, cheese, pimento and peas.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix in cooked macaroni.
Cover and keep warm over very low heat until ready to serve.
Garnish with parsley sprigs. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add water and chicken base.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in noodles and salt.
Add broccoli, garlic powder, milk and cubed cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil. Beat until combined.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until well combined.
Spread batter in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 25 (2 x 3-inch) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine ingredients, less 1 cup cheese; blend with fork.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out one hour before baking; bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
It will be rather sticky.
Drop by teaspoonful in sifted powdered sugar.
This is on a sheet of wax paper.
Roll dough (teaspoon size) in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spareribs aloha
directions: Place ribs in shallow pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off fat.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over ribs.
Bake 45 or 50 minutes longer.
Baste often.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until lemon-colored.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add this alternately with milk.
Stir in all 5 extracts.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan in a preheated 355° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cake is good for several days if it is around that long!!

title: poor man's soup
directions: Cut potatoes (skin on), tomatoes and onions up into chunks in large stew pot.
Fill the pot with water until vegetables are covered.
Add tomato sauce and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
(Makes about 6 servings.)

title: impossible pie
directions: Place
all
ingredients
into blender at one time.
Mix well and pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour. When
done
crust
will be on bottom, custard in the middle and coconut on top.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into pieces and place on greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Brown sausage in skillet, then drain off fat.
Cut links in slices.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top during baking.
This can be prepared the night before.
Cover and refrigerate. Breakfast cooks without effort.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle half of cheese over batter.
Pour in rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 425°.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Dice hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Put into crock-pot on low.
Add barbecue sauce.
Cook for 2 hours or longer.

title: cool strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake in flat pan.
As soon as cake is done, punch holes with a toothpick or knife in cake.
Pour 2 cups boiling water in Jell-O; mix well.
Pour over cake.
Put strawberries on top.
Mix pudding as directed on package and pour over berries.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Best if chilled overnight or as much as 8 hours.

title: autumn evening supper
directions: Mix potatoes, 7 cheese slices, green onions, dressing and pimiento lightly.
Spoon into an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with smoked sausage, cut into six equal portions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly baked.
Top with 3 slices of cheese, cut in half diagonally.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.

title: potato soup with rivels
directions: Bring the chicken stock to a boil in a 4-quart stockpot.
Add the diced potatoes; cook until tender.
Add the butter, milk and celery leaves.
Bring to a simmer; add salt and pepper to taste. In a small bowl, stir the beaten egg into the flour.
Stir with a fork until you have a grainy mixture.
Sprinkle small amounts at a time into the soup, stirring all the while with a wooden fork. Cook the rivels in the soup for 15 minutes.
Be careful with these rivels, as they will lump up.
Serve with parsley garnish.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine ground chuck, milk, catsup, bread crumbs, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Line pie plate with pastry and fill with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss cheese with Worcestershire sauce; sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix ingredients together and crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: braised quail
directions: Combine flour and pepper.
Dredge quail in mixture and set aside.
Melt bacon drippings in Dutch oven.
Brown quail on both sides.
Remove quail from Dutch oven and discard any remaining drippings.
Combine milk and the next three ingredients in a Dutch oven, stirring to mix.
Add quail.
Cover and cook over low heat, basting frequently, 30 minutes or until done.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Sprinkle the soup and
milk mixture with the spices and pour into an ungreased casserole.
Add the chicken.
Spoon the soup mixture over the chicken.
Serve over rice or wild rice.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add oil and eggs. Mix well.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or 1
hour in Bundt pan.
Cover top of bread with foil after 40 minutes so it won't get too brown.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes. Loosen with knife. Turn out onto waxed paper.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars and cream together.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Roll in balls, then roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
While hot, place Kiss on top.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and grate raw potatoes.
As mound of grated potatoes build, sprinkle with lemon juice to maintain color.
Mix grated sweet potatoes with ingredients.
Bake in well-greased dish at 350°.
As pudding cooks and browns, turn or fold bottom and outer edges throughout the pudding mixture.
Continue process until done, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken in greased casserole dish; sprinkle with 4 ounces cheese.
Add soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle 1 cup stuffing mix over the top and the oleo. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Heat meat.
Add onion and garlic and saute for 3 minutes. Cook until brown; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Remove meat mixture from heat; set aside.
Rinse and drain kidney beans in strainer.
Toss 1 cup of the shredded cheese and kidney beans.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix apple, celery and mayonnaise. Toss until both are well coated with mayonnaise. Serve in a chilled bowl. Top with walnuts and put a border of lettuce around.

title: brownies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs; mix well. Add flour and other ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: lemon jello bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove and pour glaze over top.
Punch holes before glazing.

title: made from scratch brownies
directions: Melt cocoa, oil and butter in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar and add eggs and vanilla.
Beat like mad.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Place mixture in square (8 x 8-inch) pan which has been well-buttered on all sides.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: chunky italian soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in a Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring until beef crumbles and is no longer pink; drain.
Return mixture to pan.
If you chose to cook with ground beef and sausage, there is no need to cook the sausage.
Just slice it into 1/4 inch pieces and add to mixture after beef is cooked.
Stir in tomatoes, next 7 ingredients and if desired, chili powder; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans and next 3 ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked pasta.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese. Yields:
10 cups.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed for layer cake. In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, marshmallows and coconut. Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Spread between layers and on top of cake. Melt chocolate chips and margarine. Spread over cake while warm.

title: tipsy cranberries
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place cranberries and sugar in ovenproof dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Add the brandy.
Stir.
Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Freeze while preparing filling.

title: strawberry bread pudding
directions: In small pan, combine undrained strawberries and cornstarch. Cook and stir over medium heat, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Stir in food coloring.
Spread evenly over bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add bread cubes.
Stir to moisten.
Carefully pour custard mixture over berries.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, if desired. Serves 6.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Crumble bacon into bottom of pie crust.
Cook onion in butter until soft.
Mix in beaten eggs, milk and Swiss cheese.
Season with pepper and nutmeg (optional).

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix Shoe Peg corn, drained.
Add green beans, drained.
Add drained pimento.
In small skillet, melt margarine. Add chopped onion and bell pepper and saute until tender.
Add to corn mixture.
Add sour cream last.
Blend well with a spoon.
Add salt.
Grease a casserole dish with margarine.
Pour in mixture. Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Top with dabs of margarine and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and take casserole out.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and return to hot oven until cheese is melted (about 30 seconds).

title: baked chicken breast with dressing
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish and cook approximately 12 to 15 minutes.

While this is baking, mix the package dressing mix according to instructions on the package. After chicken breasts have cooled slightly, place a patty of dressing on top of the chicken breasts, cupping your hand over it to make it fit to the top.
Place slice of Swiss cheese over dressing.
Mix contents of the can of cream of mushroom soup (or cream of chicken or cream of celery) with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over top of chicken.
Cover with a lid and cook for an additional 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add soup and sour cream; season with salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Put dressing on bottom of oven dish and layer squash and dressing alternately, ending with dressing on top.
Pat with several pieces of butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in 2 tablespoons butter with a pastry blender until well blended.
Beat 1/4 cup butter; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Pour batter into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in butter in a large skillet 3 to 4 minutes or until pork is cooked.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Heat rice in skillet until thoroughly heated.
Push rice to sides of skillet forming a well or nest in the center.
Pour egg into well and cook until set, stirring once.
Stir rice into eggs. Add the vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato buns
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in salt water until soft.
Pour off water and mash.
Set aside to cool.
Add flour and roll into thick, ropelike strips on floured board and lightly flatten.
Cut into squares and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream or dice and fry onion in butter or margarine until tender. Add a small can of cream.
Heat this mixture and pour over potato buns.
Serve hot.

title: peggy's cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage or hamburger meat along with the onions.
Set aside on paper towel to drain excess grease.
Cut cheese up and mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler or use a slow cooker.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve with crackers and/or chips.
Meat can be eliminated if you desire.
I've found that sausage just adds a little more flavor to this dip.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Blend shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add water to dates and add with nuts to flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Put in long baking dish. Place sliced potatoes on top of ground beef, then place sliced onions on top of potatoes.
Add the mushroom soup, then add 3/4 can of water.
Pour over top.
Add frozen mixed vegetables on top and bake for 1 1/2 hours, until potatoes are tender.

title: speedy salad
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Fold in cream. Fold in remainder of ingredients. Chill.

title: fruited wild rice
directions: Soak raisins for several hours in Grand Marnier or other liqueur or microwave on high until boiling.
Cool at room temperature.
Prepare rice according to box instructions.
Stir in fruit, cinnamon, salt, and pepper.
Cool.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Blend butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately ending with flour. Fold in flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open door.

title: oven fried cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl toss cauliflower with oil. Place cauliflower flowerets in a single layer on two rimmed baking sheets.

title: drunkard's soup
directions: In large kettle saute bacon until crisp; set aside.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add barley and saute until very lightly browned.
Add onion and continue to cook until onion is tender and barley is lightly browned.
Stir in flour, paprika and 1 cup beef stock.
Cook over low heat until most of liquid is absorbed.
Add rest of stock, sauerkraut, bacon (crumbled), salt and bay leaf and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add sausage slices and cook for additional 20 minutes.
Garnish each bowl with sour cream.

title: old-time lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Add water slowly.
Add melted butter and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: speedy green bean salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, vinegar and mustard.
Pour over green beans and potatoes.
Chill.
Makes 10 servings of 1/2 cup each.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and orange peel in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add water to orange juice to measure 3/4 cup and combine with flour mixture. Stir in egg and cranberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven 60 - 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: maple-mustard pork tenderloin with apples
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Trim fat from pork.
Place on broiler pan coated with cooking spray.
Combine mustard, 2 tablespoons syrup, chopped rosemary and salt and pepper; brush over pork. Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of pork.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or thermometer reads 160° (slightly pink).
Place a nonstick pan with cooking spray over medium-high heat until hot. Saut apples 5 minutes.
Reduce to medium-low.
Add 4 tablespoons maple syrup; simmer 12 minutes until tender.
Cut pork crosswise. Spoon apples over pork.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and mustard together and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Serve over chow mein noodles. Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with softened cream cheese and other ingredients.
Roll into ball and chill.
Chop pecans and roll cheese ball in pecans.

title: natures salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Mix well before use.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: quick applesauce
directions: Peel apples and cut up into large pieces.
Add sugar, cinnamon and lemon.
Microwave 12 to 15 minutes on High.
When apples are soft, use a hand mixer and blend.

title: lebanese beef and green beans
directions: Cut beef in bite-sized pieces. Sprinkle heavily with cinnamon and salt.
Heat olive oil in medium-sized saucepan. Add the beef and brown it on all sides over relatively high heat. Add the green beans, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over Lebanese rice.

title: chocolate toffee bar
directions: In 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish, arrange cracker squares to cover bottom of dish.
In 1-quart casserole, place butter and brown sugar.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir well.
Blend in confectioners sugar, cornstarch, salt, coconut and nuts.
Spread on crackers.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces on top.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Let stand for a few minutes, then spread melted chocolate pieces.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bars.
Add Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: strawberry bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, coconut, 1/3 cup strawberry gelatin, ground almonds, almond extract and enough red food coloring to tint mixture to a strawberry color.
Chill until firm.
Form small strawberry shapes (1/2 teaspoon).
Sprinkle remaining gelatin in a flat dish.
Roll strawberries in it to coat.
Dye some almond slivers in green food coloring.
Dye and use these for stems.
Use green decorating icing for leaves.

title: butter beans in savory sauce
directions: Combine beans, water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving the liquid.
Add enough water to the liquid to measure 1 cup; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Stir in mustard, bean liquid and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice and pimiento.
Pour sauce over beans. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and tomato
directions: Boil water with salt, add macaroni.
While macaroni is cooking, put oil in pan, add onion and brown lightly.
Add tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Drain macaroni.
When onion and tomato mixture begins to boil, add cooked macaroni.
Cook until mixture thickens.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and jello. Heat until dissolved. Remove from heat and add sugar, baby food and cream cheese. Chill until thick. Fold in Cool Whip and pecans. Let chill.

title: diabetic cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until dough forms a ball.
Beat in thoroughly, 1 egg at a time.
Continue beating mixture until smooth and velvety. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Push down bumps after baking.

title: breast of chicken in wine(serves 4)
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.
Place between wax paper and pound out chicken breasts until approximately 3/8-inch thick.
Salt and pepper breasts and roll in flour.
Heat in skillet 1/2 cup butter.
Cook breasts in hot butter over low heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Add mushrooms; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Drain off excess butter.
Add cup of cream and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.
Transfer breasts to warm platter.
Add the wine to liquid in skillet; bring to a rapid boil and cook until sauce is reduced to creamy consistency.
Spoon sauce over the chicken breasts and serve while hot.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Put a layer of crushed crackers in bottom of casserole.
Layer oysters on top of crackers.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers of crackers, oysters, salt and pepper.
Add butter, melted, over top with layer of crushed crackers.
Pour carton of whipping cream over all.
Bake at 350° until crackers are golden brown.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare topping with one cup of the milk and vanilla as directed.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Blend and then beat at high for 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Chill in pie shell at least 4 hours.

title: crab salad
directions: Amounts vary as to the size of salad desired.
Toss with salad dressing of your choice or leave plain and add choice of dressing when served.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain Mexicorn. Add bell pepper, cucumbers, onion and mayonnaise. Cover and chill. Add chopped tomato before serving.

title: pineapple sundae cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool cake.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions.
Add softened cream cheese.
Cover cooled cake with pudding/cream cheese mixture.
Drain crushed pineapple and cover cake.
Add Cool Whip and top with walnut pieces.

title: broccoli and pasta (ziti)
directions: Saute onion and garlic, then add broccoli.
Continue cooking 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Boil ziti according to package instructions; strain and save 1/2 cup of ziti water to mix with broccoli.
Combine broccoli and ziti together with freshly ground Romano or Parmesan cheese, along with black pepper to taste.
For a little bit of color, saute a few strips of red sweet peppers with the onion and garlic (optional).
Serves 8.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar until light.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in peaches.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Very good.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Split Twinkies in half.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies (creamy side up).

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, celery, mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of mixture. Sprinkle package of onion soup over top of chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Combine all the ingredients, except water and tomatoes.
Spoon the meat mixture into the cabbage leaves and roll-up and fasten with a toothpick.
Pour tomatoes and water over rolls.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: roasted beef tenderloin in a bag
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread butter, oil and salts on all sides of beef.
Roll in cheese and bread crumbs (patting it on all sides).
Place in brown grocery bag.
Fold and close bag with paper clips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave for about one hour.
Tenderloin should be pink.
If you want it more done, let it bake longer.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Add 1 stick softened oleo, orange juice, sugar and egg yolks, beaten.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in large casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon on top.
Bake in medium oven until done, about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt butter. Stir in cocoa.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until smooth. Pour into buttered pie pan (no crust) and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, soda, and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugars, and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes.

title: coconut pies
directions: In double boiler, put milk to heat.
In bowl mix the rest of ingredients.
Prebrown 2 pie shells and set aside.
Mix and add to heated milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add coconut (approximately 8 to 12 ounces); add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring and mix.
Pour into pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix and place in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, buttermilk and butter for 1 1/2 minutes. Then add the remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Stir in soup.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add other ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry glazed chicken
directions: Pound or beat filets to thin. Beat egg and add milk in a dish. Dip filets in milk/egg mixture, then shake or mix in Bisquick to coat. Refrigerate to cool and set coating 20 minutes. Heat in a boiler on low heat the strawberry glaze and add sliced strawberries. Stir occasionally. Heat oil in frying pan and fry filets until golden brown. Spoon glaze over filets just before serving.

title: pistachio-coconut surprise
directions: Combine sour cream and pudding mix.
Add coconut and pineapple and stir until blended.
Chill and then serve.

title: peach marshmallow icebox cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Cool slightly.
Add marshmallows.
Be sure to blend well.
Cool.
Add peaches and egg whites.
Place alternate layers of cookie crumbs and whipped cream.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, chopped onion and chopped pepper until tender; drain.
Pour milk over cracker crumbs to soften.
Mix all ingredients together good.
(Save 1/2 cup of cheese to sprinkle on top.)
Pour in well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
You will need extra confectioners sugar to roll balls in.
These can be frozen.

title: breakfast treats
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar, and baking powder together. Cut in Crisco.

title: butter flavored oleo
directions: Get the "possum"; clean him.
Get a large bottle of good red wine.
Sprinkle a few drops on the possum.
Take a good drink of this wine to see if it is still good wine.
Stomp him; cuss him and beat him with a stick and sprinkle a few more drops of wine on him. Take another big drink of the wine to see if it is still good.
Put another drop or two of wine on ham.
Take another big drink of wine to see if it is still good.
Put a few sweet potatoes in the pan with the possum.
Add a bunch of salt and pepper and a few more drops of wine.
Take a large drink of wine to see if it is still good.
Put into the oven about an hour.
Go look at him and put a drop or two of wine on him.
Take another big slug of wine to see if it is still good.
A little later on, look at him again.
Add a little possum to the wine.
By then, it is smelling so bad just throw the possum, sweet potatoes and pan away and drink the rest of the wine.
This is the best way to cook a possum.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let stand 2 hours until watery.
Cook until done.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Bring to a boil and add jello.
Cool.
When cold, put in jars and put in freezer.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon, onion, celery and pepper until light golden brown. (Drain off excess fat.)
Add flour and continue frying until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except catsup.
Mix well; shape into loaf.
Place in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Spread catsup over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten slightly with hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
